l Black]\r\n[bg=red][bg=70][color=black]this is red in red[/color][/bg][/bg]\r\n[bg=black]\r\n[bg=blue,70]this is blue in black[/bg]\r\n[/bg][/font][/color]\r\n\r\n[/bg]\r\n\r\n\r\n[#=contents][/#]\r\n[code]\r\n[bg=grey,310px,left][color=white][font=Tahoma][size=4][align=center][b]Contents[/b][/align][/size][/font][/color][bg=white,300px][bg=270px]\r\n[b][size=3][u]Basic Tags[/u][/size][/b]\r\n[url=#b]Bold[/url]\r\n[url=#it]Italic[/url]\r\n[url=#ul]Underline[/url]\r\n[url=#hl]Horizontal Line[/url]\r\n[url=#br]Linebreak[/url]\r\n[url=#url]Url[/url]\r\n[url=#url2]Inline Url[/url]\r\n[url=#anch]Anchor[/url]\r\n[url=#anch2]Anchor style2[/url]\r\n[url=#link1]Local Link[/url]\r\n[url=#link2]Page Link[/url]\r\n[url=#code]Code[/url]\r\n[url=#pre]Pre[/url]\r\n[url=#q]Quote[/url]\r\n[url=#spoiler]Spoiler[/url]\r\n[url=#font]Font (family)[/url]\r\n[url=#size]Text Size[/url]\r\n[url=#col]Text Color[/url]\r\n[url=#list]List items[/url]\r\n[url=#alignc]Alignment[/url]\r\n[url=#icons]Icons[/url]\r\n[url=#img]Image[/url]\r\n[url=#img2]Banner, Thumb[/url]\r\n[url=#yt]Video (Youtube)[/url]\r\n[url=#flash]Flash[/url]\r\n\r\n[b][size=3][u]Advanced Tags[/u][/size][/b]\r\n[url=#bg]Background[/url]\r\n[url=#tab]Tables[/url]\r\n\r\n[url=#more]More Examples[/url]\r\n[url=#contents]Code for this contents section[/url]\r\n\r\n[/bg][/bg]\r\n[/bg][/code]\r\n\r\n[bg=grey,310px,left][color=white][font=Tahoma][size=4][align=center][b]Contents[/b][/align][/size][/font][/color][bg=white,300px][bg=270px]\r\n[b][size=3][u]Basic Tags[/u][/size][/b]\r\n[url=#b]Bold[/url]\r\n[url=#it]Italic[/url]\r\n[url=#ul]Underline[/url]\r\n[url=#hl]Horizontal Line[/url]\r\n[url=#br]Linebreak[/url]\r\n[url=#url]Url[/url]\r\n[url=#url2]Inline Url[/url]\r\n[url=#anch]Anchor[/url]\r\n[url=#anch2]Anchor style2[/url]\r\n[url=#link1]Local Link[/url]\r\n[url=#link2]Page Link[/url]\r\n[url=#code]Code[/url]\r\n[url=#pre]Pre[/url]\r\n[url=#q]Quote[/url]\r\n[url=#spoiler]Spoiler[/url]\r\n[url=#font]Font (family)[/url]\r\n[url=#size]Text Size[/url]\r\n[url=#col]Text Color[/url]\r\n[url=#list]List items[/url]\r\n[url=#alignc]Alignment[/url]\r\n[url=#icons]Icons[/url]\r\n[url=#img]Image[/url]\r\n[url=#img2]Banner, Thumb[/url]\r\n[url=#yt]Video (Youtube)[/url]\r\n[url=#flash]Flash[/url]\r\n\r\n[b][size=3][u]Advanced Tags[/u][/size][/b]\r\n[url=#bg]Background[/url]\r\n[url=#tab]Tables[/url]\r\n\r\n[url=#more]More Examples[/url]\r\n[url=#contents]Code for this contents section[/url]\r\n\r\n[/bg][/bg]\r\n[/bg]\r\n\r\n\r\n','2012-08-10 22:59:29'),(41,1,3,'kimsufiseedbox',0,'Seedbox setup on a Kimsufi 2G','A step by step guide on a couple of methods of turning a cheap Kimsufi 2G into a Seedbox','[center][color=#0261a3][size=5][font=Arial Black]KIMSUFI 2G SEEDBOX GUIDE[/font][/size][/color][/center]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nOk we get a lot of questions about the best seedbox out there etc.  So i decided to write a guide on how to setup a [color=blue][url=http://www.kimsufi.com/fr/]Kimsufi 2G[/url][/color] as a seedbox.\r\n\r\n[size=4][u][b]Sections of the guide[/b][/u][/size]\r\n\r\n- [url=#where]What site should i order my Kimsufi 2G from?[/url]\r\n\r\n- [url=#why]Why should i choose a Kimsufi 2G?[/url]\r\n\r\n- [url=#order]The ordering process[/url]\r\n\r\n- [url=#x2go]Installing the X2Go client on you own system (Windows and Ubuntu machines)[/url]\r\n\r\n- [url=#gui]Server end setup with X2Go[/url]\r\n\r\n- [url=#cli]Server end setup with CLI[/url]\r\n\r\n- [url=#win]I cant live without Windows and im prepared to pay twice as much for the Server to avoid Linux[/url]\r\n\r\n[size=4][u][b]I recommend[/b][/u][/size]\r\n\r\nIf your brave i highly recommend the use of Deluge with a Remote GUI on your desktop.  The Kimsufi 2G is far from the most powerful Server in the world. Not using the Remote Desktop and doing things from a distance via Deluge is by far the least CPU and RAM intensive option.  When your moving a lot of data this could quite possibly translate to greater upload and download speeds.  Especially with a lot of torrents.\r\n\r\n[#=where][size=4][b][u]Which site should i order from in my Country[/u][/b][/size]\r\n\r\n[url=http://www.kimsufi.com/fr/]Main Kimsufi/OVH[/url] (Unlimited Transfers)\r\nAndorra\r\nAnonymous (your ordering under a false ID so go for Unlimited)\r\nAustralia\r\nBelgium\r\nFrance\r\nFrench Guyana\r\nFrench Polynesia\r\nFrench South Territories\r\nGuadeloupe\r\nLuxembourg\r\nMartinique\r\nMonaco\r\nNew Caledonia\r\nRÃ©union\r\nSt Pierre and Miquelon\r\nSwitzerland\r\nWallis and Futuna\r\n\r\n[url=http://www.kimsufi.ie/]Ireland Kimsufi/OVH[/url] (5TB per month then shaped to 10Mbps)\r\nCanada\r\nRepublic of Ireland\r\nUnited States of America\r\n\r\n[url=http://www.kimsufi.co.uk/]UK Kimsufi/OVH[/url] (5TB per month then shaped to 10Mbps)\r\nUnited Kingdom\r\n\r\n[url=http://www.isgenug.de/]German Kimsufi/OVH[/url] (5TB per month then shaped to 10Mbps)\r\nAustria\r\nGermany\r\n\r\n[url=http://www.isgenoeg.nl/]Netherlands Kimsufi/OVH[/url] (5TB per month then shaped to 10Mbps)\r\nNetherlands\r\n\r\n[url=http://www.kemsirve.es/]Spain Kimsufi/OVH[/url] (5TB per month then shaped to 10Mbps)\r\nArgentina\r\nBolivia\r\nChile\r\nColombia\r\nCosta Rica\r\nDominican republic\r\nEcuador\r\nEl Salvador\r\nGuatemala\r\nHonduras\r\nMexico\r\nNicaragua\r\nPanama\r\nParaguay\r\nPeru\r\nSpain\r\nUruguay\r\nVenezuela\r\n\r\n[url=http://www.kimsufi.pl/]Poland Kimsufi/OVH[/url] (5TB per month then shaped to 10Mbps)\r\nPoland\r\n\r\n[url=http://www.kimsufi.it/]Italy Kimsufi/OVH[/url] (5TB per month then shaped to 10Mbps)\r\nItaly\r\n\r\n[url=http://www.kemeda.pt/]Portugal Kimsufi/OVH[/url] (5TB per month then shaped to 10Mbps)\r\nBrazil\r\nPortugal\r\n\r\n[url=http://www.kimsufi.cz/]Czech Kimsufi/OVH[/url] (5TB per month then shaped to 10Mbps)\r\nCzech Republic\r\n\r\n[url=http://www.kimsufi.lt/]Lithuania Kimsufi/OVH[/url] (5TB per month then shaped to 10Mbps)\r\nLithuania\r\n\r\n[url=http://www.kimsufi.fi/]Finland Kimsufi/OVH[/url] (5TB per month then shaped to 10Mbps)\r\nFinland\r\n\r\n[url=http://www.kimsufi.sn/]Senegal Kimsufi/OVH[/url] (5TB per month then shaped to 10Mbps)\r\nSenegal\r\n\r\n[url=http://www.kimsufi.com/tn/]Tunisia Kimsufi/OVH[/url] (5TB per month then shaped to 10Mbps)\r\nTunisia\r\n\r\n[url=http://www.kimsufi.com/ma/]Morocco Kimsufi/OVH[/url] (5TB per month then shaped to 10Mbps)\r\nMorocco\r\n\r\n[color=red]If people are aware of countries and who they are supposed to order through please inform me and i will add them to the list\r\nAlso regarding the 5TB limit if anyone orders from some of these alternatives can they please check their manager and tell me if it lists a limit.  I have more than a sneaking suspicion that this 5TB limit is just a copy over from an old version of the OVH site and doesnt in fact exist anymore but as i order from OVH direct i cant confirm this. If you can confirm or deny the 5TB limit i would love to know[/color]\r\n\r\nIf the 5TB limit really worries you there may be ways to get around the default country but they are not easy and likely against the terms of service.  I will leave you to imagine them yourself.\r\n\r\nOVH will most likely ask you to verify your identity.  They will want a copy of your Drivers Licence/Passport, A Utility Bill and a copy of your CC with all except the last 4 numbers obscured.  Again i will leave you to decide if you can handle this or wish to take other measures that i will not provide advice on.\r\n\r\n[#=why][size=4][b][u]Why should i choose a Kimsufi 2G over other seedboxes?[/u][/b][/size]\r\n\r\n- Its not really just a seedbox its actually a dedicated server so you have a lot more options than your usually seedbox slot.\r\n\r\n- For the price of a small seedbox slot you get 1TB of storage and unlimited torrents not to mention the whole 100Mbps link all to yourself.\r\n\r\n- If your able to order direct to from OVH in France you also get Unlimited transfers. Most of the country specific sites suggest they limit the 2G to 5TB and once you pass that reduce speed for the rest of the month to 10Mbps.  Its country dependant sorry and im slowly compiling a list. Im also looking into if this limit in fact really exists.\r\n\r\nBut if your doing over 5TB a month is that really such a hardship? \r\n\r\n- Most Seedbox slots are actually a shared Kimsufi 2G or Kimsufi 16G so why not have the whole box for the same price or less?\r\n\r\n- The option to use a GUI rather than CLI if you so desire (i will cover both options)\r\n\r\n- Choice of Torrent client ( i will cover both KTorrent for those who must use a GUI and Deluge with remote GUI for those a little more comfortable with the CLI)\r\n\r\n[color=red][b]A final note. Please do not post this guide on other sites.  At least not until its finished and tested and not without asking me. Its been a lot of work converting my knowledge and what others have taught me into a simple guide and im fairly certainly even once done i will spend some time solving problems and modifying it.  So i dont want it posted everywhere unless its working properly please.[/b][/color]\r\n\r\n[#=order][size=4][b][u]The Ordering Process[/u][/b][/size]\r\n\r\nGo to Kimsufi.com (its in French so i recommend Google Chrome for automatic translation or Firefox with the appropriate plugin).  Once you have finished the setup process all contact and the server will be in the language of your choice :)\r\n\r\nOnce translated it should look like this\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=D026_4FE84012][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=D026_4FE84012&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nClick the Commander button for the server of your choice the Kimsufi 2G.  Although this guide will work just as well for any of the Kimsufi range.\r\n\r\nChoose your set-up method.  In this case you want to choose \"Bureau distant\" or Remote Desktop.  I will use this for both methods.  Having the Remote desktop available is nice and costs nothing so why lock yourself into CLI only?\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=B662_4FE842B3][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=B662_4FE842B3&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nNext step is choose which one.  \r\n\r\nChange it to your desired language and choose Ubuntu Desktop 12.04 for the reason its 64 bit out of the box (very important if you choose anything larger than the 2G) and its also the most current Long Term Support Version of Ubuntu.\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=64E2_4FE84444][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=64E2_4FE84444&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nAfter this you should get this page.\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=7297_4FE86EB3][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=7297_4FE86EB3&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nI then recommend you change the lease term to 1 month as you can always renew later with ease and you might end up with a Celeron rather than an Atom processor.  The Atom is much better if you can get it.  \r\n\r\nHeck you may not even want the box long term.  A month or two with this baby may very well solve you ratio issues on multiple sites for months or years.\r\n\r\nOnce done it should now look like this\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=830E_4FE86EB3][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=830E_4FE86EB3&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nClick Continuer and you should now see this\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=B75B_4FE84653][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=B75B_4FE84653&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nClick \"New contract\" and it should extend the page asking for more details like this.\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=F6DB_4FE8474F][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=F6DB_4FE8474F&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nFill it out as your paranoia permits :)  Once done you should get this\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=A1CA_4FE847B7][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=A1CA_4FE847B7&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nChoose a password for your management console and continue.\r\n\r\nIt will now confirm the contact information (that may very well be garbage other than the email address).  Continue\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=9FE3_4FE84910][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=9FE3_4FE84910&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nIt will then do the usual contract confirm tickbox show here.  We all know you will read this carefully and never do anything naughty with this Dedicated server.\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=3FBD_4FE8496F][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=3FBD_4FE8496F&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nNow your at the final confirm and choose payment screen.  I think you can handle the payment yourself :)\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=D5FF_4FE849C9][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=D5FF_4FE849C9&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nYou have now ordered a Kimsufi 2G so wait on the emails and prepare to set it up.\r\n\r\nOnce the server is setup you should get an email like this that will contain your login details\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=B4E9_4FEC4BBE][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=B4E9_4FEC4BBE&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\n[#=x2go][/#][size=4][b][u]Installing the X2Go Client on your home machine[/u][/b][/size]\r\n\r\n- Windows\r\n\r\nThe files can be found here and need Admin rights\r\n\r\n[url=http://anonym.to/?http://code.x2go.org/releases/binary-win32/x2goclient]X2Go Client for Windows[/url]\r\n\r\n- Ubuntu (also likely other versions of Linux)\r\n\r\nCheck your package manager.  I found it there in seconds :)\r\n\r\nPlease tell me if you need me to flash this section out but its fairly basic so i wont go to heavily into the steps.\r\n\r\n[#=gui][/#][size=4][b][u]Using X2Go to login to your server[/u][/b][/size]\r\n\r\nUsing the login details enter them into X2Go like this add a name (i called mine \"Seedbox\") and session type needs to be set as \"Custom Desktop with the command \"gnome-session --session=gnome-classic\"\" like this\r\n\r\n[color=red]Note:  If you server hasnt been up very long you may need to put the IP address instead of hostname as it may not resolve yet[/color]\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=9EC3_4FEC5562][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=9EC3_4FEC5562&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nClick your session on the right and enter your password like this and then click ok\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=EEB4_4FEC503B][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=EEB4_4FEC503B&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nEventually a window should open like this\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=DD9D_4FEC5AB5][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=DD9D_4FEC5AB5&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nCongratulations you are now logged into your soon to be seedbox :)  \r\n\r\n[size=2]Next we install a[/size]\r\n- FTP so we can transfer files too and from the seedbox\r\n- Torrent program (I will cover Ktorrent and Deluged)\r\n\r\nOpen Ubuntu Software Centre by clicking \"Applications\" and then \"Ubuntu Software Centre\"\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=42D9_4FEC5BF8][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=42D9_4FEC5BF8&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nIt should look like this\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=1170_4FEC5DCD][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=1170_4FEC5DCD&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\n- Remove Transmission (Optional) because its junk and it may be set as default for .torrent files.\r\n\r\nType Transmission into the search bar and it should bring up a list like this.  A green tick means its currently installed so we know thats the one we want to remove.  Click Remove\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=CB6F_4FEC5F25][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=CB6F_4FEC5F25&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nA window will pop up asking you to authenticate.  Ubuntu asks before installing anything and requires a password.\r\n\r\nEnter the password you used to login via X2Go\r\n\r\nWait till its finished\r\n\r\n- Install vsftpd\r\n\r\nSearch \"vsftpd\"\r\n\r\nInstall it the same way you removed Transmission\r\n\r\n- Install KTorrent (or skip if your choosing to go with Deluge)\r\n\r\nAs above but be aware its going to have to install a heap of other stuff to make KTorrent work ok as its designed for the KDE desktop not Gnome.  But it does all of this for you so let it do its thing :)\r\n\r\n- Install Deluged (or skip if you chose KTorrent)\r\n\r\n[color=red]Note: Deluged is what you want not Deluge[/color]\r\n\r\nAs above\r\n\r\n[size=2]Its now time to configure[/size]\r\n- FTP\r\n- Deluge (if you chose deluge)\r\n\r\nFTP\r\n\r\nOpen the terminal (sorry guys i cant see an easy way around this your going to have to use the command line once)\r\n\r\nYou will find it under \"Accessories\" and \"Terminal\" as show here\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=A468_4FEC6A06][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=A468_4FEC6A06&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nThis will open up\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=056C_4FEC6A55][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=056C_4FEC6A55&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\n[code]gksudo gedit[/code] \r\n\r\nHit enter and enter your password when prompted\r\n\r\nThis will open the text editor in \"super user\" mode.  That way you can edit the needed files.  If your not in super user mode you will only be able to open the following files in \"read only\" mode. It should look like this\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=666E_4FEC72D7][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=666E_4FEC72D7&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nClick Open\r\nClick \"File System\"\r\nDouble click \"etc\"\r\nScroll down until you find a file named \"vsftpd.conf\"\r\nDouble click it\r\nThe file should open\r\nLook through the file until you find the following lines\r\n\r\n[quote]# Allow anonymous FTP? (Beware - allowed by default if you comment this out).\r\nanonymous_enable=YES\r\n#\r\n# Uncomment this to allow local users to log in.\r\n#local_enable=YES\r\n#\r\n# Uncomment this to enable any form of FTP write command.\r\n#write_enable=YES[/quote]\r\n\r\nChange \"anonymous_enable=YES\" to \"anonymous_enable=NO\"\r\nDelete the # in front of \"local_enable=YES\" and \"write_enable=YES\"\r\n\r\nIt should now look like this\r\n\r\n[quote]# Allow anonymous FTP? (Beware - allowed by default if you comment this out).\r\nanonymous_enable=NO\r\n#\r\n# Uncomment this to allow local users to log in.\r\nlocal_enable=YES\r\n#\r\n# Uncomment this to enable any form of FTP write command.\r\nwrite_enable=YES[/quote]\r\n\r\nClick Save\r\nClose Gedit\r\n\r\nFTP is now working skip to the [url=#KTorrent]next part if you chose KTorrent[/url]\r\n\r\nBack to the terminal (sorry) for those who chose Deluge.  Hopefully its still open\r\n\r\n[code]deluged\r\necho \"username:password:10\" >> ~/.config/deluge/auth (exchanging username and password for your chosen username and password.  It does not need to be the same as the server username and password.)\r\nsudo apt-get install deluge-console [color=red]Note: Nothing will appear when you type it this is normal.[/color]\r\ndeluge-console\r\nconfig -s allow_remote True\r\nexit[/code]\r\nYou should return to the normal Terminal prompt\r\n[code]pkill deluged\r\ndeluged[/code]\r\n\r\nInstall Deluge on your home computer\r\nRun deluge on your home computer.\r\nGo to \"Preferences -> Interface\" and untick \'Classic Mode\' to disable it.\r\nRestart deluge. You should now see the Connection Manager pop up.\r\nRemove the localhost daemon.\r\nClick \"Add\" and for \'Hostname\' enter your server\'s IP.\r\nLeave the Port as default (58846).\r\nEnter the Username & Password you added to the authentication file then finish by clicking \'Add\'. A green tick should now appear as the status for the host you just added.\r\n(Optional) Expand \"Options\" and select \"Automatically connect to selected host on startup\" and \"Do not show this dialog on start-up\".\r\nClick \"Connect\" and the connection manager pop up box should disappear.\r\n\r\nHeres a picture of my local deluge controlling my seedbox. It\'s an elegant and nice way to run your torrents.  Much nicer than rTorrent/ruTorrent IMO.\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=1EB8_4FF6F2D2][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=1EB8_4FF6F2D2&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\n[color=blue]You can now use Deluge on the server from your home machine.  This is by far the best way i know of to run a seedbox :)[/color]\r\n\r\n[#=KTorrent][/#][size=2]How to use KTorrent (if you chose to)[/size]\r\n\r\nUpload your torrent files to the server using FTP.  By default it should place those files in /home/desktop/\r\n\r\n[color=red]I usually use Filezilla as my FTP program.\r\nIf people need a guide on how to use Filezilla please let me know and i will add one here[/color]\r\n\r\nDouble click (or right click and choose open with KTorrent) any .torrent file to open the torrent with KTorrent.  It should look like this\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=7C6B_4FEC7718][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=7C6B_4FEC7718&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nClick OK to start downloading :)\r\nAs for the rest of KTorrent i will let you find a guide but its similar to uTorrent.  Any questions please ask in the Help and Support Forum not this thread.\r\n\r\n[#=cli][size=4][b][u]Server end Setup via SSH[/u][/b][/size]\r\n\r\n\r\nThis will be by far the fastest and best way to setup your seedbox.  In fact its so quick and easy i dont even need to post screenshots.  This will cover only a Remote Deluge Setup.\r\n\r\nFor anyone using Linux your likely to be familiar with SSH.  Just open a Terminal and type\r\n[quote]ssh username@(IP Address or name of your server)[/quote]\r\n\r\nThe first time you login to a server you will get a warning like this as it wont have an RSA Key fingerprint for the server yet.  if you get it a second time you may have security issues.  Consult a professional at that point.  But the first time you login and get this the answer is \"yes\".\r\n\r\n[quote=Terminal]The authenticity of host \'ks000000.kimsufi.com (1.1.1.1)\' can\'t be established.\r\nRSA key fingerprint is 00:00:00:00:00:00:00:00:00:00:00:00:00:00:00:00.\r\nAre you sure you want to continue connecting (yes/no)?[/quote]\r\n\r\nEnter the password when asked and your now logged into the remote server and can use the terminal like you were sitting at the machine.\r\n\r\nFor those of you using windows you are going to need a program to do this.  PuTTY is a free Open Source program commonly used.  You can download it [url=http://www.chiark.greenend.org.uk/~sgtatham/putty/download.html]here[/url]\r\n\r\n[color=red]Im going to get on my Windows machine soon and test PuTTY for and subtle differences and to do a connection guide.[/color]\r\n\r\nNow from here im going to copy and paste some code from a Linux terminal.  If PuTTY has some differences my apologies but it should be exactly the same once you login to your server.\r\n\r\nOnce your logged in you should see something like this\r\n\r\n[quote=Terminal]Welcome to Ubuntu 12.04 LTS (GNU/Linux 3.2.13-xxxx-std-ipv6-64 x86_64)\r\n\r\n * Documentation:  https://help.ubuntu.com/\r\nUbuntu 12.04 LTS\r\n\r\nserver    : (server number)\r\nip        : (Server IP)\r\nhostname  : (hostname)\r\n\r\n\r\nx packages can be updated.\r\nx updates are security updates.\r\n\r\n*** System restart required ***\r\nLast login: Sun Jul  1 05:46:23 2012 from (your IP address hopefully if anything)[/quote]\r\n\r\nIf you see update waiting and you usually will lets do some updates\r\n\r\nYou should be able to copy and paste this directly from the guide to your terminal. Each line is a new command.  Enter password when asked. If you get a yes/no question the answer you want is in capitals. Y or N will do in 99% of cases.\r\n\r\nsudo apt-get update (this updates your package list)\r\nsudo apt-get upgrade (this runs updates)\r\n\r\nNext we install FTP and configure it\r\n\r\nsudo apt-get install vsftpd\r\nsudo vi /etc/vsftpd.conf\r\n\r\nThis will open of all things a CLI Text Editor.  Who remembers those?\r\n\r\nAnyway go through that file using your keyboard only and change the following\r\n\r\n[quote=code]anonymous_enable=YES needs to be changed to anonymous_enable=NO\r\n#local_enable=YES needs to be changed to local_enable=YES\r\n#write_enable=YES needs to be changed to write_enable=YES\r\n[/quote]\r\n\r\nNow hit \":\" Which should create a : at the bottom of your terminal\r\nAfter the : type \"x\" and hit Enter\r\nYou should return to the SSH Terminal with the changes saved (i hope).  Then type this to restart vsftpd with your changes\r\n\r\nsudo service vsftpd restart\r\n\r\nOk so FTP server is now sorted\r\n\r\nNow its time for Deluged\r\n\r\nsudo apt-get install deluged\r\nsudo apt-get install deluge-console\r\necho \"username:password:10\" >> ~/.config/deluge/auth (change username and password to your chosen ones, this is not the server ones if you value security)\r\ndeluge-console (this opens the deluged console to make some changes)\r\nconfig -s allow_remote True\r\nexit\r\n\r\nYou should now be back at your normal SSH prompt\r\n\r\npkill deluged\r\ndeluged\r\n\r\nOk you should now be setup and ready to open a remote Deluge client and use your seedbox.  \r\n\r\nCongratulations less than an hour well spent.\r\n\r\n[#=win][/#][size=4][b][u]If you have to run Windows and are willing to pay for it[/u][/b][/size]\r\n\r\nYou can have Windows Server 2008 on it if you are not proficient with Linux but it will cost you, last I checked it is EUR15/Mo.  This literally doubles the cost of the server so im not sure its such a great option\r\n\r\nsome screenshots for the ordering:\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=DA85_4FE887F4][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=DA85_4FE887F4[/img][/url]\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=AB32_4FE887F4][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=AB32_4FE887F4[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nunless you want SQLServer for some reason...\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=417A_4FF7F083][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=417A_4FF7F083&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\n3. Then just get the bare minimum option like the one above and 64bit unless for some reason you prefer 32bit that is available too, cheapest option unless you plan to do more than seedbox.\r\n\r\n4. Once you get it set up you will get a Windows Remote Desktop Access so is like being there.\r\n\r\n5. Install Firefox unless you prefer IE (yuck and unsafe) with Adblock Plus and NoScript for safety.\r\n\r\n6. IS VERY IMPORTANT TO STAY SAFE AS THIS IS A SERVER OPEN TO THE WORLD AND WILL BE ATTACKED.\r\n\r\n7. Configure the Windows Firewall to open ports for FTP (DO NOT USE THE STANDARD 21 ONE BUT SOMETHING ELSE like for example 2348 again for safety) and uTorrent.\r\n\r\n8. Install Windows Defender for Virus protection. Others will not work on a Server installation. But this one is fine in my experience.\r\n\r\n9. Install and configure FileZilla Server (this one again is safe in my experience) and again for safety only allow writing when you need it. Then turn it off again.\r\n\r\n10. Install uTorrent configure, create folders etc...\r\n\r\n11. Personally I run torrents in an encrypted partition (there are several free softwares to do this) that I mount manually each time. So your activity is hidden just in case.\r\n\r\nThanks to [url=/user.php?id=70679]barumba[/url] for the Windows Section of the guide\r\n\r\n[size=4][b][u]Links to other useful guides[/u][/b][/size]\r\n\r\n[url=/articles.php?topic=rtorrent]DrkNess\'s rTorrent setup guide[/url]\r\n\r\nAny changes to this guide you feel are required should be emailed to \"Clownius\".  Thank You','2012-08-10 23:05:31'),(42,1,0,'tutorials',0,'Help and tutorials section','','[center][color=#0261a3][size=5][font=Arial Black]Help and tutorials[/font][/size][/color][/center]\r\n\r\nHere you will find helpfull guides and tutorials.\r\n\r\nIf you cannot find the help you need here then please post in the [url=/forums.php?action=viewforum&forumid=6]Help & Support Forum[/url]\r\n\r\nMost help requests will be answered faster and at least as well in the forums as they will be by the staff or first line support, but if you must contact the staff use the message form on the [url=/staff.php]Staff[/url] page. ','2012-08-30 09:50:12'),(43,0,1,'forbiddencontent',0,'Forbidden Content','This is the Forbidden Content List','[center][color=#0261a3][size=5][font=Arial Black]Forbidden content[/font][/size][/color][/center]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n[color=#0261a3][size=4][font=Arial Black][b]Please note that by violating these rules you will be banned permanently...!!![/b][/font][/size][/color]\r\n\r\n\r\n[*]NO Underage (below 18) content.\r\n[*]NO Child Porn.\r\n[*]NO True Rape.\r\n[*]NO Beast.\r\n[*]No Snuff.\r\n[*]No Main Stream Content Allowed.\r\n[*]NO Child Birth.\r\n[*]NO Programs/.exe Files except for porn games.\r\n[*]NO Password protected files or folders.\r\n[*]No Archived media except for large pictorrents.+250 pics.(uploaders choice)\r\n[*]No rar Scene releases,you need to unrar them to make screens anyway.\r\n\r\n\r\nUNDER NO CIRCUMSTANCES POST OR REQUEST ANY OF THIS MATERIAL\r\n\r\n1) NO Child/Underage Porn (under 18).\r\nThis includes drawings/hentai such as lolicon & similar, anything that is overtly underage is strictly not allowed.\r\nDon\'t push it, don\'t even think about it, just don\'t do it.\r\nStaff decisions at this private site are final, you can accept it or leave, do not argue.\r\n\r\n2) NO True Rape.\r\n\r\n3) NO Beast or Snuff.\r\nYes this also includes drawing & animation, with some hentai, tentacle etc, being an obvious exception.\r\nHowever they MUST be genuine hentai titles, that is the title/s is primarily concerned with sex.\r\nSome anime titles contain sexual elements/scenes but it\'s not the prime focus, they have no place here.\r\nAny deaths or serious injury in such content should be incidental & not part of or due to sexual acts.\r\n\r\n4) NO Underage models or incidental by-standers (non-nude or otherwise).\r\n\r\n5) NO Child Birth.\r\n\r\n6) NO Password protected files or folders unless password is provided... Don\'t waste everyone\'s time and don\'t charge anyone for the damn password...\r\n\r\n7) NO video files packed in a .rar or .zip extension\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[anchor=specific] [/anchor]\r\n[color=#0261a3][size=4][font=Arial Black]Please check this list for specific sites and stars who are banned on the tracker[/font][/size][/color]\r\n\r\n[*]Alexandra Quinn pre-dating 1991/2. All of Alexandra\'s legal titles star her with D-cup breast implants so anything else must not be uploaded here.\r\n[*]bd company\r\n[*]Beach Cabin series or similar originating from dubious Russian/Ukrainian websites.\r\n[*]best-teens.com\r\n[*]Bieyanka Moore, ALL\r\n[*]Christina Model - Anything from \'05 or earlier.  She was under 18 at the time.\r\n[*]Color Climax / Vicom / Blue Vanities / Filmfare: - All titles.\r\n[*]dark company\r\n[*]Galitsin content, ALL\r\n[*]Girls Gone Wild: Ultimate Spring Break, On Campus Uncensored, Totally Exposed UNcensored & Beyond, College Girls Exposed/Sexy Sorority Sweethearts, Spring Break 2003 or any GGW titles starring Ashley Alexandra Dupre/Eliot Spitzer scandal call girl.\r\n[*]Hannah/hannah-fans.com/Hannah_UK/Hannah motel room etc, etc.\r\n[*]hotlols\r\n[*]Karina World\r\n[*]little agency\r\n[*]LittleLupe.com, ALL\r\n[*]lolitanetworks/lolitasex.com\r\n[*]lolitas holiday\r\n[*]lolitashouse\r\n[*]ls models (ls barbie, ls land, ls valentine, ls little guests, ls batman, ls forbidden fruit, ls Little Pearl, ls stunning dolls, ls builder, ls show, ls stars, ls dream, ls Lively Pers)\r\n[*]Misty Regan titles pre-dating 1981: Champagne Orgy; Diamond Collection original series #2,#3,#9,#11; Inside Desiree Cousteau; Rolls Royce #6; Sound Of Love; Three Ripening Cherries; Udderly Fantastic; Urban Cowgirls; Velvet High; High School memories\r\n[*]Muntinlupa Philippines scandal - ALL videos\r\n[*]mylola.info\r\n[*]Pink-Teens\r\n[*]preteen agency\r\n[*]Sebastian Bleisch - ALL titles\r\n[*]sundolls\r\n[*]sunlolitas\r\n[*]teenfuns/angelfuns/fallenangelfuns/fm-teens etc\r\n[*]Traci Lords Titles, ALL.\r\n[*]ukraine angels\r\n[*]video2000\r\n\r\n\r\nThis list is not exhaustive','2012-08-30 09:37:27'),(44,1,6,'avatartutorial',0,'Avatar tutorial','How to add an Avatar','[center][color=#0261a3][size=5][font=Arial Black]AVATAR TUTORIAL[/font][/size][/color][/center]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nFirst, find an image that you like, and that is within the [url=/articles.php?topic=avatar]rules[/url]. Then you will have add it to \r\n\r\n[url]http://xxx.freeimage.us/[/url]\r\n\r\n1. Select an image you\'ll like for a long time and resize it to a maximum height of 400 pixels. It can be smaller and will be resized if necessary to a maximum of 150x250 pixels automatically.\r\n\r\n2. Upload it to xxx.freeimage.us\r\n\r\n3. You will get 4 links. None of these work if used from start to finish! Just copy the url from your browser and forget the 4 links. So we get something like this (taken from my avatar)\r\n\r\n[code]http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=EC0A_4E9317FF[/code]\r\n\r\nYou need to change this to\r\n\r\n[code]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image-XXXX_XXXXXXXX[/code]\r\n\r\nthen add your image - replace XXXX_XXXXXXXX with your image letters/numbers, [b]then add[/b] .jpg\r\n\r\nso it should look like\r\n\r\n[code]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image-EC0A_4E9317FF.jpg[/code]\r\n\r\nThe above is taken from my avatar ! Don\'t link to it.\r\n\r\n4. Go to \"Settings\" at the top right and paste it in \"Avatar Url\". If all is fine, your avatar will show straight away in the profile.\r\n\r\nBest of luck.\r\n\r\nThanks to Combin for the original article.','2012-08-10 22:59:38'),(45,1,5,'uploadchecklist',0,'Uploading Checklist ','A helpful guide to uploading','[center][color=#0261a3][size=5][font=Arial Black]Uploading checklist[/font][/size][/color][/center]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[b]Uploading guide - a quick checklist[/b]\r\n\r\n\r\nFor everyone that wants to follow the \'upload\' path, here is a little something that everyone should know:\r\n\r\n 1. [url=/articles.php?topic=utorrentupload]Uploading with uTorrent for dummies[/url]\r\n 2. [url=/articles.php?topic=vuzeupload]New Uploaders Torrent Description Help[/url]\r\n 3. [url=/articles.php?topic=winscreenshots]How to create screenshots (Windows)[/url]\r\n 4. [url=/articles.php?topic=linscreenshots]How to create screenshots (Linux)[/url]\r\n\r\nThese will all be moved away from the forum into articles.\r\n\r\n','2012-09-07 15:49:44'),(46,1,5,'presentation',0,'Guide to Presentations','A useful guide to making a presentation','[center][color=#0261a3][size=5][font=Arial Black]Guide to presentations[/font][/size][/color][/center]\r\n\r\n\r\nYou might have come here after uploading something that was deleted, or you are lucky enough to have seen this tutorial before you uploaded something. No matter how you got here though this is the place where you can read about uploading torrents to the tracker and all that this involves. \r\n\r\nBefore you continue reading here though make sure you have read and understand the rules for uploading as stated here ([url=http://empornium.mooo.com/articles.php?topic=upload]Uploading rules[/url]).\r\n\r\nNote: The tracker will not accept torrent files larger than 1 MB in size! [color=#FF0000]Stil true?[/color]\r\n\r\n\r\n[*]Only Upload allowed content: Check to see if the file you want to upload isn\'t on the forbidden list ([url=/articles.php?topic=forbiddencontent]Forbidden list[/url])\r\n[*]Check for dupes: Always check that your file hasn\'t already been posted on the tracker. If it has, then make sure it\'s not the same format otherwise it will be considered a duplicate and be deleted. For a detailed description of what is considered a dupe look here ([url=http://empornium.mooo.com/articles.php?topic=upload]dupe details[/url]).\r\n[*]Add a good description: Describe what site, genre, actors, year this is from, resolution and fileformat and the name of the file.  If you don\'t know,try to find out where its from.  Google the name of the file and see if you can find anything.   Then describe the content and plot.\r\n\r\n[b]What NOT to use as a description[/b]\r\n\"This was posted on \"blabla\" before and now its here.\"\r\n\"The screens say it all...\"\r\n\"I found this on my hard drive-enjoy!\"\r\n\"Those who likes this already knows what it is...\"\r\nNon of the above bits tell anything about the actual content of the torrent.\r\n\r\nTop Tip: Where to find Descriptions or Dvd Covers\r\n[*]adult dvds\r\n[*]cduniverse\r\n[*]adultwiki\r\n[*]iafd\r\n[*]adultfilmdatabase\r\n[*]excaliburfilms\r\n\r\n\r\n[*]Add proper screenshots: Create a screenshot gallery or a good number of preview pics.  For a 30 min to 1 hour video it just isnt enough with 3 pics even if they are really good. There are great tutorials in the Tutorial Forum,and making screens is not very hard these days. Here is one: [url=/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=1412]Creating Screencaps With ThumbnailMe[/url]\r\n[*]Upload pics to an APPROVED imagehost: Well, time to upload the preview pics/screens and then the first thing to do is to check what pichost you can use in this article ([url=http://empornium.mooo.com/articles.php?topic=approvedimg]Approved pichosts[/url]).\r\n','2012-09-03 11:41:40'),(47,1,3,'connectable',0,'How to get Connectable','A guide to getting connected','[center][color=#0261a3][size=5][font=Arial Black]Geting connectable[/font][/size][/color][/center]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nI thought i should share this with the community because there are a lot of people who are still not connectable and it might help people track down a specific problem. I tweeked a few things and a few lines to make it easier to read because it is a LOT to read.\r\n\r\n[b]First of all don\'t assume you are connectable.[/b]\r\n \r\nMany people assume they are connectable, because they are successfully torrenting. That however is not always the case.\r\n\r\n[b]How do i know if i am connectable or not?[/b]\r\n\r\nUse the [color=blue][u][url=/user.php?action=connchecker]Conn-Checker[/url][/u][/color].\r\n\r\nThe Connectability Checker is used to check you are connectable through your torrent client.\r\n\r\nYou must enter your external IP address and the port you are [b]currently connected[/b] on with your torrent client.\r\n\r\nAt the bottom of this article you can find some graphical help in determining what port you have set in your torrent client.\r\n\r\n\r\n[b]What does it mean to be connectable?[/b]\r\n \r\nBeing connectable means other peers in the swarm can make connections to you, you can make connections to other peers without being connectable your self, if the other peers in your swarm are good enough torrent citizens to be connectable.\r\n \r\n\r\n[b]Why does it matter?[/b]\r\n \r\nWell, Many private trackers restrict people who aren\'t connectable, and even on some sites no seed bonuses are credited to people who aren\'t. most importantly people who aren\'t connectable hurt the swarm. Each peer that isn\'t connectable is limited to sharing with only peers who are connectable. If the number of peers who aren\'t connectable is low the result is unnoticeable, But the higher the percentage goes the slower the swarm becomes until it dies at the point when all peers are unconnectable. There\'s no one left to connect to.\r\n \r\n\r\n[b]Why am I unconnectable? Well maybe...[/b]\r\n \r\n[*]Lack of proper port forwarding.\r\n[*]TURN OFF DHT, PEER EXCHANGE, LOCAL PEER DISCOVERY\r\n[*]Bandwidth oversaturation, incoming or outgoing.\r\n[*]Too many torrents started at once.\r\n[*]Too many connections per torrent, or total.\r\n[*]ISP blocking chosen port\r\n[*]Router not P2P friendly\r\n[*]ISP modem contains router features\r\n[*]ISP proxying or firewalling your connection\r\n \r\n\r\n[b]What can I do about it?[/b]\r\n \r\nSometimes nothing. for instance if your ISP has you behind a proxy server that blocks incoming requests. If their only blocking certain ports you can change the port you use, and if their throttling (this has nothing to do with becoming connectable.) you could use uTorrent or \r\nAzureus and enable encryption. It may be that you are trying to torrent from a place of business with routers, proxy servers, firewalls, and/or traffic shaping software, or appliances like websense. If your even lucky enough to get a torrent running at all, but being connectable is out of the question.However, most cases being connectable is fun, easy and can be done without spending any money at all.\r\n \r\n\r\n[*][b]First[/b], make sure any anti-virus software you use isn\'t blocking any ports you use for torrenting \r\n[*][b]Second[/b], set your firewall to give full access to your torrent program, don\'t block it in any way. \r\n[*][b]Third[/b], set your bandwidth limits in your torrent software, if you let it use all your bandwidth to share information with your peers there may not be enough to browse the internet or communicate with the tracker. Not being able to communicate with the tracker in a timely fashion may cause the tracker to list you as unconnectable when you are in fact connectable. Run a speed test at Speedtest.net - The Global Broadband Speed Test to find your up and down speeds, set your client for around 80% outgoing and 90% to 95% incoming. These numbers aren\'t set in stone so feel free to play a little but make sure you are connectable first and be prepared to change them back if you run into problems. \r\n[*][b]Fourth[/b], Don\'t shutdown or start your software with a lot of torrents running. whats a lot? I think 3 would be OK, but 10 is out. The point is shut down and start your torrents individually or groups of 2 or 3 with a pause between, and if you shutdown your computer wait for your start up programs to finish before starting your torrents back up. \r\n[*][b]Fifth[/b], limit the number of connections per torrent and total connections. defaults will usually work but maybe shrink it down more if your still showing up unconnectable. \r\n[*][b]Sixth[/b], make sure your modem doesnt have routing features. Some newer modems have features but are not heavily configurable so the easiest thing to do is to turn these features off if possable. \r\n[*][b]Seventh[/b], Your router may just not be good at handling P2P protocalls like bitorrent which require many connections made over a short time. All routers have a limited number of connections they can handle being open at any one time, some leave connections open for too long, most notably LINKSYS WRT54G/GL/GS routers. There are fixes for this but it involves upgrading to beta or possibly third-party firmware, which always carries risks. If you think this applies to you follow the faq on uTorrent\'s or whatever client you are using site but proceed with the utmost caution.\r\n[*][b]Eighth[/b], Try using ports between 65,000 and 65,500 this works better for most people, and do not use software like PeerGuardian2. TURN OFF DHT, PEER EXCHANGE, and LOCAL PEER DISCOVERY\r\n[*][b]Finally[/b], and this can be the hardest part for most people, follow one of many very good guides concerning port forwarding.Port Forwarding Guides Listed by Manufacturer and Model - PortForward.com is a good place to start.\r\n \r\n1. Setup your computer to a static ip there are very good guides for this at portforward select your operating system and follow the guide.\r\n \r\n2. Next you need to setup your router to forward the correct ports to your computer. A step by step guide for just about every router is located at PortForward\'s Other Guides - PortForward.com , scroll down and select port forwarding guides by router. Just select your router, and \r\nthen click on your bit-torrent client for specific steps on how to correctly configure your setup. Remember to use the IP address you assigned your computer in step one. Also, the port number can be almost anything you want, but I suggest using something over 50,000. \r\n\r\n3. If you run a firewall you\'ll need to set it up to allow the correct traffic. go to Port Forwarding Guides Listed by Manufacturer and Model - PortForward.com select the firewall you have and follow the steps.\r\n \r\n4. Once you\'ve set up all of that, make sure your client is running, then go to Open Port Check Tool\r\nenter in the port you\'re using.This page will tell you whether your port is open, stealthed, or closed.If it is open, then you should be Connectable.\r\n  \r\n\r\n[b]Why have your computer set to a static IP?[/b]\r\n \r\nOn networks where DCHP (Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol) is running you get an IP address issued automatically when you connect.In theory this is great but until you connect you donâ€™t know what this IP address will be. Most routers have a set range of IP addresses to use \r\nbut how these are issued depends on the make/model of the router.So if you set up port forwarding for the IP currently issued to your PC today, will it work tomorrow or even after a reboot? Maybe but if the PC gets issued a different IP address your PC will never see the data on the ports you forwarded.How can you be sure of always having the port forwarded to the right computer port â€“ simple set up a static IP address. That way every timethe computer restarts it will be the same IP address and the port forwarding will work perfectly.\r\n \r\n\r\n[b]Why be connectable (or what happens when you are not?)[/b]\r\n \r\nA 1gig torrent is uploaded. The uploader starts seeding. 9 leechers jump on to the torrent. The torrent is going very slow. He has already seeded 5GB but no one has completed. Turns out they are all unconnectable. This means that the uploader needs to send 1gig of data to each of them. If he stops seeding before they have completed the torrent it will dry up and no more data will be transferred.\r\n \r\n\r\n[b]Another example:[/b]\r\n\r\nYou find the torrent. There\'s 10 seeders. You\'re hopeful for good speeds. Your PC starts looking for bits. The speed is slow and you only seem to be connecting to 1 seeder.... WTH!!! Well if 9 are not connectable this means you\'ll not be able to leech very much from them and at very slow speeds. \r\n\r\nThe essence of this guide is not to get you individually faster download speeds but the reverse; faster upload speeds. The more people that are directed to this guide and follow it properly the faster the swarm will become which means faster download speeds for everyone.\r\n \r\n\r\n[b]Find port in Deluge: Open Deluge and Open the Settings.  Choose the one that says network[/b]\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=D1DC_500A6DCF][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=D1DC_500A6DCF&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\n[b]Find port in Utorrent:Open Utorrent and Open the Setup Guide from the preferences. \r\nOptions -> Setup Guide.[/b]\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=0DF8_500836CF][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=0DF8_500836CF[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nIt can also be found by selecting preferences-settings-connection.\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=A0FA_5008350A][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=A0FA_5008350A[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nIf you need to setup a port in Utorrent check this link:[url]http://www.utorrent.com/help/guides/connection-setup/[/url]\r\n\r\nI hope this helps people get connectable because being connectable is good for you and the swarm in the long run.:smile1:\r\n\r\nThanks to KnightsOfTheRound who originally posted this on the forums','2012-09-03 10:59:19'),(48,0,1,'ranks',0,'User Classes','The different user classes and what they mean','[center][color=#0261a3][size=5][font=Arial Black]User classes[/font][/size][/color][/center]\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n[font=Arial Black][size=2]User Classes[/size][/font]\r\n[anchor=app][/anchor]\r\nAll promotions in the normal user classes happen automatically once you meet the minimum requirements. Do not ask staff to promote you.\r\n\r\n[b][color=#92a5c2]Apprentice[/color][/b]\r\n[*]The default class of new members.\r\n[*]Must maintain a ratio at or above your [url=/articles.php?topic=ratio]required ratio[/url]\r\n[*]Note that you will be put on the limiter if your ratio drops below your [url=/articles.php?topic=ratio]required ratio[/url] at any time\r\n\r\n[anchor=perv][/anchor]\r\n[b][color=#4Ec89B]Perv[/color] [/b]\r\n[*]Must have been be a member for at least 1 week\r\n[*]have uploaded at least 10GB \r\n[*]have a ratio at or above 0.7\r\n[*]The promotion is automatic when these conditions are met\r\n[*]Note that you will be automatically demoted if your ratio drops below 0.65 at any time\r\n\r\n[anchor=gperv][/anchor]\r\n[b][color=#3c3]Good Perv[/color] [/b]\r\n[*]Must have been be a member for at least 4 weeks\r\n[*]have uploaded at least 25GB \r\n[*]have a ratio at or above 1.05\r\n[*]The promotion is automatic when these conditions are met.\r\n[*]Note that you will be automatically demoted if your ratio drops below 0.95 at any time.\r\n[anchor=sperv][/anchor]\r\n[b][color=orange]Sextreme Perv[/color] [/b]\r\n[*]Must have been be a member for at least 13 weeks\r\n[*]have uploaded at least 1TB \r\n[*]have uploaded 50 torrents \r\n[*]have a ratio at or above 1.05\r\n[*]The promotion is automatic when these conditions are met.\r\n[*]Note that you will be automatically demoted if your ratio drops below 0.95 at any time.\r\n\r\n[anchor=smutp][/anchor]\r\n[b][color=#00f]Smut Peddler[/color] [/b]\r\n[*]Must have been be a member for at least 26 weeks\r\n[*]have uploaded at least 10TB \r\n[*]have uploaded 250 torrents \r\n[*]have a ratio at or above 1.05\r\n[*]The promotion is automatic when these conditions are met.\r\n[*]Note that you will be automatically demoted if your ratio drops below 0.95 at any time.\r\n\r\nOccaisonally the staff will promote users to any rank at the staff\'s discretion, anyone asking to be promoted won\'t be.\r\n\r\n\r\n[font=Arial Black][size=2]Staff Classes[/size][/font]\r\n[anchor=mod][/anchor]\r\n[b][color=black]Mod Perv[/color][/b]\r\n[*]Can edit and delete any uploaded torrents.\r\n[*]Can also moderate user comments in forums and torrent presentations and disable accounts.\r\n[*]Don\'t ask us, we\'ll ask you.\r\n\r\n[anchor=admin][/anchor]\r\n[b][color=#606]Admin Perv[/color][/b]\r\n[*]Can do just about anything.\r\n\r\n[anchor=sysop][/anchor]\r\n[b][color=#8B0000]Sysop[/color][/b]\r\n[*]Da boss\r\n \r\n\r\n[font=Arial Black][size=2]Other[/size][/font]\r\n[anchor=fls][/anchor]\r\n[b]Front Line Support[/b]\r\n[*]Not a rank as such, any user may be appointed as a [b]FLS[/b] - they help out with the running of the site and have some mod powers and responsibilities, be very nice to them.\r\n[*][b]IMPORTANT NOTE[/b] - FLS are users who volunteer to help us run the site well, please treat them with some respect. \r\n\r\n[anchor=donor][/anchor]\r\n[b]Donor[/b]\r\n[*][img]http://empornium.mooo.com/static/common/symbols/donor.png[/img] - Has donated money to torrents.empornium.me. To donate please message the Sysop.\r\n[anchor=title][/anchor]\r\n[b]Customised title[/b]\r\n[*]Conferred by mods at their discretion or bought from bonus credits.\r\n\r\n ','2012-09-07 01:53:42'),(49,0,1,'approvedimg',0,'Approved Image hosts','This is a list of all the approved image hosts to be used at Empornium','[center][color=#0261a3][size=5][font=Arial Black]Approved image hosts[/font][/size][/color][/center]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThe following Pichosts have been approved:\r\n\r\n[whitelist]\r\n \r\n\r\nIf you want to have a pic host approved post a link in [b][url=/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=749]this topic[/b], and Staff will take a look at it! \r\n\r\nWe encourage members to use [b][url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/]http://xxx.freeimage.us/[/url][/b] as a host for screens and pics here.  ','2012-08-27 20:39:15'),(50,1,4,'irc_register_nick',0,'03. How to register your nickname on IRC','Guide on how to register your nickname on the Empornium IRC Network','[align=center][b][size=2]How to Register your nickname on IRC[/size][/b][/align]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nRegistering your nickname on Empornium IRC provides a number of benefits. The most notable of these is that registering your nickname prevents other people from using it. Once a user starts using the nickname, they will be asked to â€˜identifyâ€™ to it with a password. If they fail to do so, their nickname will be changed. This helps to stop people posing as you.\r\n\r\nOnce you register your nickname, you can be added to the auto voice and op lists in other peopleâ€™s channels. This enables you to be a permanent staff member in channels. You are also entitled to a vhost once you have been registered.\r\n\r\nRegistration provides you with many benefits and is completely free.\r\n\r\nTo register your nickname on Empornium IRC, you must first be using it. If you are not currently using it, change to it with the command:\r\n\r\n[quote]/nick <nickname>[/quote]\r\n\r\nFor example:\r\n\r\n[quote]/nick CrazyUser[/quote]\r\n\r\nOnce you are using the nickname, you may register it in one of two ways. In any client, use the following command:\r\n\r\n[quote]/ns register <password> <e-mail>[/quote]\r\n\r\nFor example:\r\n\r\n[quote]/ns register supersecretpassword crazyuser@hotmail.com[/quote]\r\n\r\nFollowing this, you will be not get an e-mail you are done. The e-mail is needed only to recover your password.\r\n\r\nEach time you connect and start using the registered, you will be told that â€œThis nick is owned by someone elseâ€. You must â€˜identifyâ€™ to it using the following command:\r\n\r\n[quote]/ns identify <password>[/quote]\r\n\r\nFor example:\r\n\r\n[quote]/ns identify supersecretpassword[/quote]\r\n\r\nIf you use mIRC, you can load the following script into the Remotes section of your script editor (press alt+R to access this) to identify you automatically. Just replace â€˜YOURPASSWORDHEREâ€™ with your actual password:\r\n\r\non 1:NOTICE:*This nickname is registered and protected*:?: {\r\n   if ($nick == NickServ) {\r\n      ns identify YOURPASSWORDHERE\r\n   }\r\n}\r\n\r\non 1:NOTICE:*This nick is owned by someone else*:?: {\r\n   if ($nick == NickServ) {\r\n      ns identify YOURPASSWORDHERE\r\n   }\r\n}\r\n\r\nIf you require help, come and see us in [url=http://torrents.empornium.me/irc.php]#empornium-help on irc.emprn.tk[/url]. Users who have registered with NickServ will automatically get voiced in the channel when they join.','2012-09-10 17:48:20'),(51,1,4,'irc_multi_nick',0,'04. Grouping Nicknames together on IRC.','Useful if you want to connect from more than one computer at a time.','[align=center][b][size=2]Grouping nicknames together on IRC[/size][/b][/align]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nSo youâ€™ve registered your nick, but have more than one computer/device that you join IRC from. You might be wondering â€œdo I need to register a new nick and have people add that nick to access lists as well? Certainly there must be an easier way.â€\r\n\r\nWell luckily for you, there is. You are able to group nicks together so that permissions and other data are shared among accounts. Some of the items that are shared include (but are not limited to): channel ownership, permission levels (owner, halfop, etc.) on channels, group info that was provided when you registered, password, and virtual host. Pretty much anything your single nick has associated with it will be associated with the group of nicks that you have registered.\r\n\r\nHereâ€™s how to group a nick to one that you already have registered:\r\n\r\n* Switch to the nick that you want to group\r\n[quote]/nick JayneCobb[/quote]\r\n\r\n* Enter the following command in the server/status window: \r\n[quote]/msg nickserv group [/quote] \r\n\r\n\r\n[b]Example:[/b] \r\nI want to group JayneCobb to my primary nick, MalcolmReynolds. I would type the following:\r\n[quote]/nick JayneCobb\r\n/msg nickserv group[/quote]\r\nNote: you must be identified as MalcomeReynolds when you changed your nickname.\r\n\r\nLook for nickserv to either tell you that you have joined the group of your primay nick or give you an error message.\r\n\r\nAnd just to give you the commands again, they are, in order:\r\n\r\n[quote]/nick theNewNick[/quote]\r\n[quote]/msg nickserv group main_nick password[/quote]\r\n\r\nNow what if you want to delink a nick, i.e. remove it from the group, is there some way to do that? Yes there is, you just ungrouop it by switching to the nick, and doing \r\n[quote]/msg nickserv ungrouop [/quote]\r\nDoing that will make nickserv completely drop the nick â€“ it will no longer exist, have any permissions, etc.\r\n\r\nIs there someway to delink it without ungrouping, or without it losing the permissions and other information? Not currently, although I suppose it is possible that it could end up in a future version of services, or someone could create a module that could drop a nick and register it using the credentials of the former group and preserving permissions, etc.\r\n\r\nShould you have any questions about grouping nicks, feel free to leave a comment here, or to join #empornium-help and ask in there.','2012-10-22 16:36:31'),(52,1,4,'irc_auto_join',0,'05. Add IRC Channels to automatically join','Add a list of channels to join when you connect to IRC and identify.','[align=center][b][size=2]Add IRC channels to automatically join[/size][/b][/align]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThe AJOIN command is a server-side command that keeps track of the channels you join each time you connect to Empornium IRC. If you login with your nick and identify with your password, you can join all the same channels automatically. It works no matter what client you use or where you connect from since all the details are kept on the server.\r\n\r\n* Note that your client may have an option to keep an auto-join locally. Check your documentation for details on using a client-side system if you want to keep your settings on your machine(s). This explanation will focus on the server-side system only.\r\n\r\n[u][b]What is required to join channels automatically?[/b][/u]\r\n\r\nYour nickname has to be registered, and you have to identify before you can use the AJOIN command. Additionally, the channel that you want to join has to be registered. Remember that you can only be in 100 channels, so you can only include 100 channels in your AJOIN list.\r\n\r\n[u][b]How do I join a channel automatically?[/b][/u]\r\n\r\nTo add a channel to the list of those that you join every time you connect to Empornium IRC (your AJOIN list), use the following command:\r\n\r\n[quote]/ns AJOIN ADD #channel[/quote]\r\n\r\nFor instance, \r\n[quote]/ns AJOIN ADD #topgear[/quote] would add the channel #topgear to your AJOIN list.\r\n\r\n[u][b]How do I add a channel that uses a key to my AJOIN list?[/b][/u]\r\n\r\nIf the channel you want to add uses a key, you need to include the key when you use the command:\r\n\r\n[quote]/ns AJOIN ADD #channel key[/quote]\r\n\r\nFor instance, \r\n[quote]/ns AJOIN ADD #topgear hAmsT3r[/quote]  would add the channel #topgear with the channel key â€œhAmsT3râ€ to your AJOIN list.\r\n\r\nCan I just add every channel Iâ€™m in right now?\r\n\r\nYes, you can. Join all the channels you want to add, and use the command:\r\n\r\n[quote]/ns AJOIN ADDALL[/quote]\r\n\r\nThe command will also automatically include the keys for any channels to your AJOIN list.\r\n\r\n[u][b]How do I see a list of all the channels I join automatically?[/b][/u]\r\n\r\nTo see a list of all the channels on your AJOIN list, use the command:\r\n\r\n[quote]/ns AJOIN LIST[/quote]\r\n\r\nUse wild cards with this command to list only the channels on your AJOIN list that match a specific pattern. \r\nFor instance, the command [quote]/ns AJOIN LIST #top*[/quote] would return all the channels on your AJOIN list that begin with â€œ#topâ€ (for instance, #topgear).\r\n\r\n[u][b]How do I remove a channel from my AJOIN list?[/b][/u]\r\n\r\nTo remove a channel from your AJOIN list, use the command\r\n\r\n[quote]/ns AJOIN DEL #channel[/quote]\r\n\r\nFor instance, [quote]/ns AJOIN DEL #topgear[/quote] would remove the channel #topgear from your AJOIN list.\r\n\r\n[u][b]How do I delete all the channels that I join automatically?[/b][/u]\r\n\r\nTo remove all the channels from your AJOIN list, use this command:\r\n\r\n[quote]/msg NickServ AJOIN CLEAR[/quote]\r\n\r\nThe command will delete all the channels from your AJOIN list. When you connect to Empornium IRC again, you will not join any channels automatically.\r\n\r\n[u][b]What if I get banned from a channel I usually join automatically?[/b][/u]\r\n\r\nIf you are banned from a channel, please be sure to remove it from your AJOIN list, using the AJOIN DEL command above. Keeping a channel you are banned from on your AJOIN list may result in accidentally evading the ban.','2012-09-10 18:15:51'),(53,0,1,'irc_rules',0,'IRC Network and Channel Rules','Rules that have to be followed on Empornium IRC Network and in Official Channels','[center][color=#0261a3][size=5][font=Arial Black]IRC network and channel rules[/font][/size][/color][/center]\r\n\r\n[u]NETWORK RULES:[/u]\r\n\r\n[*]No harassing the Ops,Admins or Users.\r\n[*]No flooding, this includes messaging an excessive amount of lines in channel or private message within a short interval of time. Admins and Ops may enforce this rule at their discretion.\r\n[*]No mass cloning. Mass Cloning is considered multiple connections from the same IP/host to the server. You are allowed to have 2 clones. Admin reserves the right to enforce this rule at their discretion. Repeated cloning [b]will[/b] result in the automatic banning for 30 minutes.\r\n[*]Op/Oper begging is forbidden. If you get really annoying by begging for op\'s you may given a 72h ban from the server.\r\n[*]No service abuse. Abuse is determined on a case-by-case basis.\r\n[*]Profanity must be kept to tolerable levels. Words deemed by the Admin to be inappropriate for channel depending on the context within which they are used, are forbidden. Admins and Ops reserve the right to enforce this rule at their discretion.\r\n[*]Away message content is subject to the profanity rule. Messages should be kept to minimal lengths. Repeating messages are not allowed.\r\n[*]Overall conduct should be ruled by common sense. If your behavior, playful or otherwise becomes too excessive, Ops/Opers at their discretion may ask that you tone it down, or may be forced to remove you.\r\n\r\nFailing to follow any of the above rules can result in kicks, channel bans, kills, or network bans.\r\n\r\nThis server\'s staff reserve the right to deny access to anyone on this server without the benefit of prior warning or notification.\r\n\r\nBy connecting to and using this server you agree to abide and follow all rules, policies, and procedures. The admins reserve the right to add and edit rules without prior notification.\r\n\r\nN.B. We currently DO NOT allow connections from open proxies (socks and http), tor, blacklisted IP\'s or known spambots. If you are caught by the proxy checker you [b]will[/b] be banned for 72 hours. Please appeal in this thread to appeal your ban.\r\n\r\n[u]#Empornium Rules:[/u]\r\n[*] Respect â€” don\'t engage in racism or hate speech. People are entitled to different opinions.\r\n[*] Appropriate â€” think before you type, is your comment appropriate? Is it possible someone may misinterpret what you\'re saying in jest as hateful speech?\r\n[*] personal attacks, trolling/baiting or flooding (posting multiple repetitive lines or large amounts of code) of the channel will not be tolerated..\r\n[*] Use your [b]full[/b] site nickname.\r\n[*] Use [b]English[/b] only.\r\n\r\n[u]#empornium-help Rules:[/u]\r\n[*] No off topic chat. Help related only, we have #empornium to talk in.\r\n[*] No double posting. We heard you the first time.\r\n[*] Use [b]English[/b] only.\r\n\r\n[b]WE ARE NOT AROUND 24/7 PLEASE WAIT FOR YOUR QUESTION TO BE ANSWERED.[/b]','2012-09-07 01:12:35'),(54,1,3,'unseeded',0,'Reseed a torrent','How to reseed or jump on a torrent when you already have the file(s)','[center][color=#0261a3][font=Arial Black][size=6]Reseed a torrent[/size][/font][/color][/center]\r\n\r\nIf you still have the data you can reconnect to a torrent very easily.\r\n\r\nFirst download the torrent file again from the site if you do not have it.\r\n\r\nOpen the torrent file in your torrent client and simply point the location to the correct file or folder on your hard drive.\r\n\r\n \r\n[size=3][font=Arial Black]Instructions for relocating a file in utorrent[/font][/size] \r\n\r\nIn utorrent 2.1.2 you can relocate the torrent, or any part of it after you have downloaded it.\r\n\r\nStop the torrent and use the right-click menu to change to a different folder (or with a single file torrent to change the file) by:\r\n\r\n[img]http://i.imgbox.com/aahHDvKD.jpg[/img]\r\n\r\n\r\nto relocate individual files in a multi-file torrent use the right-click menu for the individual file(s):\r\n\r\n[img]http://i.imgbox.com/aahMakD4.jpg[/img]\r\n\r\n\r\nIIRC you get a prompt saying are you sure you want to save over an existing file - make sure they really are the same (I have actually backed my files up on the few occaisions I have used this) and click yes. \r\nYou will need to recheck the files (can take a loooong time for big torrents) if you want it to recognise files you already have. It ends up looking a bit weird with long form path/filenames in the folder window but it works!\r\n ','2012-09-03 11:05:54'),(55,1,6,'credits',0,'Bonus Credits','A guide to credits and the bonus system','[center][color=#0261a3][size=5][font=Arial Black]BONUS CREDITS[/font][/size][/color][/center]\r\n[#=what]What is a credit?[/#]\r\n\r\nCredits are distributed as a bonus to people who are seeding torrents. You can find your total credit amount at the top right of the page header, or on your user details page with your bonus log.\r\n\r\n[#=what]How is the credit calculated?[/#]\r\n\r\nThe amount of credits you earn per hour depends on how many torrents you are seeding. More torrents means more credits but when you are seeding more than 20 torrents per hour the extra amount per torrent is slightly less.\r\n\r\n[b]Amount of credits per hour[/b][color=black]\r\n[font=Courier New]\r\n[table][tr]\r\n[td]\r\n+----------+---------+\r\n| torrents | credits |\r\n+----------+---------+\r\n| 1        | 2       |\r\n| 2        | 3       |\r\n| 3        | 5       |\r\n| 4        | 6       |\r\n| 5        | 7       |\r\n| 6        | 8       |\r\n| 7        | 9       |\r\n| 8        | 10      |\r\n| 9        | 11      |\r\n| 10       | 12      |\r\n| 11       | 13      |\r\n| 12       | 14      |\r\n| 13       | 15      |\r\n| 14       | 16      |\r\n| 15       | 16      |\r\n| 16       | 17      |\r\n| 17       | 18      |\r\n| 18       | 19      |\r\n| 19       | 19      |\r\n| 20       | 20      |\r\n| 21       | 21      |\r\n| 22       | 21      |\r\n| 23       | 22      |\r\n| 24       | 23      |\r\n| 26       | 24      |\r\n| 28       | 25      |\r\n| 30       | 26      |\r\n+----------+---------+\r\n[/td][td]  \r\n+----------+---------+\r\n| torrents | credits |\r\n+----------+---------+\r\n| 35       | 29      |\r\n| 40       | 31      |\r\n| 45       | 34      |\r\n| 50       | 36      |\r\n| 55       | 38      |\r\n| 60       | 40      |\r\n| 65       | 42      |\r\n| 70       | 44      |\r\n| 80       | 47      |\r\n| 85       | 49      |\r\n| 90       | 51      |\r\n| 95       | 52      |\r\n| 100      | 54      |\r\n| 110      | 57      |\r\n| 120      | 60      |\r\n| 130      | 63      |\r\n| 140      | 65      |\r\n| 150      | 68      |\r\n| 160      | 71      |\r\n| 170      | 73      |\r\n| 180      | 75      |\r\n| 200      | 80      |\r\n| 220      | 84      |\r\n| 240      | 88      |\r\n| 260      | 92      |\r\n| 280      | 96      |\r\n| 300      | 100     |\r\n+----------+---------+\r\n[/td][td]  \r\n+----------+---------+\r\n| torrents | credits |\r\n+----------+---------+\r\n| 350      | 109     |\r\n| 400      | 117     |\r\n| 450      | 125     |\r\n| 500      | 132     |\r\n| 550      | 139     |\r\n| 600      | 145     |\r\n| 650      | 152     |\r\n| 700      | 158     |\r\n| 750      | 163     |\r\n| 800      | 169     |\r\n| 850      | 175     |\r\n| 900      | 180     |\r\n| 1000     | 190     |\r\n| 1200     | 209     |\r\n| 1400     | 227     |\r\n| 1600     | 243     |\r\n| 1800     | 259     |\r\n| 2000     | 273     |\r\n| 2200     | 287     |\r\n| 2400     | 300     |\r\n| 2600     | 313     |\r\n| 2800     | 325     |\r\n| 3000     | 337     |\r\n| 5000     | 437     |\r\n| 10000    | 623     |\r\n| 15000    | 765     |\r\n| 20000    | 884     |\r\n+----------+---------+\r\n[/td]\r\n[/tr][/table]\r\n[/font][/color]\r\n\r\n\r\nThe maths is: \r\nROUND( ( SQRT( 8.0 * ( COUNT( * ) /20 ) + 1.0 ) - 1.0 ) / 2.0 *20 )  per hour\r\nwhere COUNT( * ) = the total number of torrents you are seeding.\r\n\r\n\r\nCredits can be spent in the [url=/articles.php?topic=shop]bonus shop[/url]\r\n','2012-09-03 18:02:42'),(56,1,3,'rtorrent',0,'Installing and using rTorrent+ruTorrent','How to run rtorrent/rutorrent on a seedbox','[center][color=#0261a3][size=5][font=Arial Black]How to install and run rTorrent/ruTorrent on a seedbox[/font][/size][/color][/center]\r\n\r\n\r\n[size=2]Notes[/size]\r\n[*]This guide is going to make a new user named seeder1 and will install everything as if this is going to be your seed account. Feel free to change this name but do make sure you change it EVERYWHERE.\r\n[*]You can probably do more parts of this guide from the root user saving you the trouble of having to always type \"sudo\"  infront of the commands however this does allow for the problem that the user running the rtorrent program can\'t access all other files thus causing trouble with plugins of even the entire program not running. I find it safest to just do it like this.\r\n\r\n[size=2]The guide[/size]\r\n\r\nThis tutorial will guide you through the setup of a fully-featured seedbox running on a Debian or Ubuntu system, including:\r\n\r\n[*]libtorrent 0.13.0\r\n[*]rTorrent 0.9\r\n[*]ruTorrent Web UI (3.0)\r\n\r\nThis guide has been tested with Debian 6 (x86_64), Ubuntu 11.04 (x86_64) and Ubuntu 12.04 (x64).\r\n\r\nTo start, access your VPS or dedicated server via SSH (as the root user) and do the following to update your platform and install some required dependencies: \r\n[codeblock]apt-get update\r\napt-get install subversion build-essential automake libtool libcppunit-dev libcurl3-dev libsigc++-2.0-dev unzip unrar-free curl libncurses-dev\r\napt-get install apache2 php5 php5-cli php5-curl[/codeblock]\r\n\r\nNext step is to add a user under whose name the entire system is going to run.\r\n[codeblock]adduser seeder1[/codeblock]\r\nAnswer the questions asked and make sure you remember the password.\r\n\r\nAdd the user to the list of sudoers (for some basic help with the editor VI look here :[url]http://www.unix-manuals.com/tutorials/vi/vi-in-10-1.html[/url]\r\n[codeblock]vi /etc/sudoers[/codeblock]\r\nFind the part where it says \"root ALL=(ALL:ALL) ALL\" and add a new line (go to correct line, press the [ i ] key and enter what it says below. Once done press the [ esc ] key\r\n[codeblock]Seeder1 ALL=(ALL:ALL) ALL [/codeblock]\r\nSave the file and exit (in vi you do this by pressing :wq[ enter ])\r\n\r\nClose the ssh connection and restart it with the new user you just created. Then continue\r\n\r\nEnable scgi for Apache:\r\n[codeblock]sudo apt-get install libapache2-mod-scgi\r\nsudo ln -s /etc/apache2/mods-available/scgi.load /etc/apache2/mods-enabled/scgi.load[/codeblock]\r\n\r\nInstall XMLRPC:\r\n[codeblock]sudo mkdir /install;cd /install\r\nsudo svn checkout http://xmlrpc-c.svn.sourceforge.net/svnroot/xmlrpc-c/stable xmlrpc-c\r\nsudo cd xmlrpc-c\r\nsudo ./configure --disable-cplusplus\r\nsudo make\r\nsudo make install[/codeblock]\r\n\r\nIntall libtorrent:\r\n[codeblock]cd /install\r\nsudo wget http://vps6.net/src/libtorrent-0.13.0.tar.gz\r\nsudo tar xvf libtorrent-0.13.0.tar.gz\r\nsudo cd libtorrent-0.13.0\r\nsudo ./autogen.sh\r\nsudo ./configure\r\nsudo make\r\nsudo make install[/codeblock]\r\n\r\nInstall rTorrent:\r\n[codeblock]cd /install\r\nsudo wget http://vps6.net/src/rtorrent-0.9.0.tar.gz\r\nsudo cd rtorrent-0.9.0\r\nsudo ./autogen.sh\r\nsudo ./configure --with-xmlrpc-c\r\nsudo make\r\nsudo make install\r\nsudo ldconfig[/codeblock]\r\n\r\nCreate required directories:\r\n[codeblock]mkdir /home/seeder1/rtorrent\r\nmkdir /home/seeder1/rtorrent/.session\r\nmkdir /home/seeder1/rtorrent/watch\r\nmkdir /home/seeder1/rtorrent/download[/codeblock]\r\n\r\nSetup .rtorrent.rc file (rTorrent config):\r\n[codeblock]cd\r\nwget http://vps6.net/src/.rtorrent.rc[/codeblock]\r\n\r\n(Edit the settings in .rtorrent.rc, like max upload/download speed, max connected peers, etc, as needed.)\r\n[codeblock]vi .rtorrent.rc[/codeblock]\r\n\r\nInstall rTorrent:\r\n[codeblock]cd /install\r\nsudo wget http://vps6.net/src/rutorrent-3.0.tar.gz\r\nsudo tar xvf rutorrent-3.0.tar.gz\r\nsudo mv rutorrent /var/www\r\nsudo wget http://vps6.net/src/plugins-3.0.tar.gz\r\nsudo tar xvf plugins-3.0.tar.gz\r\nsudo mv plugins /var/www/rutorrent\r\nsudo rm -rf /var/www/rutorrent/plugins/darkpal\r\nsudo chown -R www-data:www-data /var/www/rutorrent[/codeblock]\r\n\r\nSecure /rutorrent:\r\n[codeblock]sudo a2enmod ssl\r\nsudo a2enmod auth_digest\r\nsudo a2enmod scgi\r\nsudo openssl req $@ -new -x509 -days 365 -nodes -out /etc/apache2/apache.pem -keyout /etc/apache2/apache.pem\r\nsudo chmod 600 /etc/apache2/apache.pem\r\nsudo htdigest -c /etc/apache2/passwords seedbox seeder1[/codeblock]\r\n\r\n(Enter a password of your choice when prompted, you will use this to log in to the ruTorrent web UI.)\r\n\r\n[codeblock]cd /etc/apache2/sites-available/\r\nsudo rm -rf default\r\nsudo wget http://vps6.net/src/default\r\nsudo a2ensite default-ssl\r\nsudo /etc/init.d/apache2 reload[/codeblock]\r\n\r\nInstall screen:\r\n[codeblock]sudo apt-get install screen[/codeblock]\r\n\r\nStart rTorrent in a detached shell using screen:\r\n[codeblock]screen -fa -d -m rtorrent[/codeblock]\r\n\r\n(To start rtorrent automatically when the VPS is booted, add the above command to /etc/rc.local)\r\n\r\nYou can now access ruTorrent at http://xx.xx.xx.xx/rutorrent/ (replace xx.xx with your server\'s IP address). You should be greeted with a login prompt, where the username is \"seeder1\" and the password is the one you set above in the \"secure /rutorrent\" section.\r\n\r\nThanks to DrkNess who originally posted this in the Tutorials Forum\r\n\r\nIf all that code scares you try the Remote Deluge setup section of the [url=/articles.php?topic=kimsufiseedbox]Kimsufi 2G Guide[/url]','2012-09-03 11:01:46'),(58,1,5,'vuzeupload',0,'Uploading with Vuze for Dummies','A  guide on how to download with Vuze','[center][color=#0261a3][size=5][font=Arial Black]Uploading with vuze for dummies[/font][/size][/color][/center]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[size=2]\r\nStep 1. Open Vuze. Click \"File\" and \"New Torrent\"\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=894D_4F78A602][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=894D_4F78A602&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nStep 2. In the pop-up window, you have to paste the [u]announce url[/u] provided by empornium, when you click \"Upload\" in the menu bar. \r\nYou also must choose whether you want to upload a single file, or a folder of files (directory).\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=E6DB_4F78A602][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=E6DB_4F78A602&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=AC37_4F798616][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=AC37_4F798616&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nI\'ll be making a single video upload:\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=1AAA_4F78A602][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=1AAA_4F78A602&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nStep 3. The pop-up window will change page, asking you to select the file you want to upload. Click browse. \r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=0785_4F798616][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=0785_4F798616&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nIn the pop-up window, browse to the file and select it.\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=9D90_4F798616][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=9D90_4F798616&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nThe file will appear in the address bar. Click \"Next\".\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=FFF6_4F78AA25][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=FFF6_4F78AA25&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nStep 4. Click \"Private Torrent\" and \"Finish\".\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=178E_4F78AA25][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=178E_4F78AA25&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nWhen Vuze is done creating the file, click \"Close\".\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=F538_4F78AA25][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=F538_4F78AA25&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nStep 5. You have created the .torrent file needed to make your upload. Go back to empornium\'s upload page and click \"Browse\" and in the pop-up window, \r\nselect the torrent file you created \r\n(it will be in either the folder \"My Documents/Vuze Downloads\" or the folder of your file).\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=5972_4F7986A1][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=5972_4F7986A1&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nStep 6. Fill the other fields of the upload form (description, tags etc) and click \"Upload Torrent\" at the bottom of the page. \r\nIt will inform you that you have successfully uploaded your torrent and will present you the torrent\'s page. \r\n\r\n:excl: [u]Now, you have to download the torrent from empornium, \r\nin order to start seeding it[/u]. \r\nFor Vuze to check the torrent and seed it:\r\n\r\nStep 7. [u]Before[/u] you download the torrent from emp, go to \"Tools\" and \"Options\". \r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=71B7_4F78B354][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=71B7_4F78B354&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nClick \"Files\" and deselect the \"Automatically download to default directory\" box. \r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=03B8_4F78CF93][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=03B8_4F78CF93&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nNow, whenever you open a .torrent file, Vuze will ask you where to save the file. Click browse and in the pop-up window go to your file\'s folder.\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=49B3_4F78D4FC][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=49B3_4F78D4FC&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nIf you don\'t deselect the \"Automatically download to default directory\" box, Vuze will start downloading the file in: \"My Documents/Vuze Downloads\". \r\nSo, if it is not there, the program will start downloading it from scratch. \r\nPause the torrent in Vuze, delete it, copy your file in the default folder and re-download the .torrent file. \r\nOr, delete the torrent in Vuze, go to Options, deselect the box, and download the .torrent file again. Now you\'ll be asked where to save, so choose the file\'s folder.\r\n\r\n\r\n[align=center] [b]Additional Settings[/b]\r\n\r\nClick \"Tools\" and then \"Options\".\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=71B7_4F78B354][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=71B7_4F78B354&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=0768_4F78B354][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=0768_4F78B354&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=D678_4F78B354][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=D678_4F78B354&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\n\r\n:excl: [u]Please Note:[/u] :excl:\r\n[/align][/size][b]\r\n[img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image-3932_4FEE1E2D.jpg[/img][u]If you get a \"missing passkey\" error[/u], it is because you are trying to seed with the .torrent file you created. Remove the torrent from Vuze and continue from Step 7.\r\n[img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image-3932_4FEE1E2D.jpg[/img][u]If a torrent gets stuck at 99% checked[/u], you probably deleted/renamed a small file in it, [i]after[/i] creating the .torrent file. As a result, Vuze is trying to find and check something that is not there anymore. Restore what you altered/deleted, and select \"Force Recheck\". If you are unable to (e.g. you changed something in a text file and don\'t remember what), remove the torrent from Vuze, create a new .torrent file and start over.\r\n[img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image-3932_4FEE1E2D.jpg[/img]If you have successfully followed the tutorial and are seeding the torrent, but you notice that your speed is unusually low, you could be non-connectable. You can have a fellow member check it for you [url=http://torrents.empornium.me/forums.php?action=viewtopic&topicid=1779] here[/url], and if you indeed are, check the [url=http://torrents.empornium.me/forums.php?action=viewtopic&topicid=1445] Guide to become Connectable[/url].\r\n[img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image-3932_4FEE1E2D.jpg[/img]If Vuze adds the torrent but, instead of checking it, it says \"Downloading\", you have not selected the folder where the files are. Remove the torrent from Vuze and continue from Step 7.[/b]\r\n\r\nThanks to eimaimpala for posting this guide in the forums originally :)','2012-09-07 15:37:48'),(59,1,6,'tags',0,'Tagging and Tags guide','A guide for tagging and tags on the site - should include anything tag related.','[center][color=#0261a3][size=5][font=Arial Black]TAGGING AND TAGS GUIDE[/font][/size][/color][/center]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[size=4]Work in Progress[/size]\r\n\r\n\r\n[size=3][b]Tags in General[/b][/size]\r\n\r\nTags are not mandatory, they are voluntary.\r\nIf you use tags, then there are [url=http://empornium.mooo.com/articles.php?topic=tag]Tagging Rules[/url] and guidelines to be followed\r\nMembers can add tags to your torrents as well as their own, even if you dont.\r\nMembers can vote on tags, either up (+) or down (-)\r\n\r\nIf you\'re going to use tags, either on your own torrents or someone elses torrents; \r\n(1) Follow the [url=http://empornium.mooo.com/articles.php?topic=tag]Tagging Rules[/url]\r\n\r\n(2) Stick with the [url=http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?action=tag_synonyms]Official Tag List[/url]. \r\n    - Use these where appropriate.\r\n    - Even if you prefer a different phrase, use the official one. The site had to pick one, that is the one we picked. \r\n    - Never add tags that are not actually a part of the clip. i.e: not.pregnant, this is a useless tag.\r\n    - Do not double up, i.e: as per rules page, do not use big.tits and big.boobs and big.knockers. Just use big.tits as it is the official tag for that specific \'bent\'. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[size=3][b]Background[/b][/size]\r\n\r\nA lot of effort and discussion has gone into the subject of tags. Some love them, some hate them. In the end Sys Ops and Admin have elected to implement the use of tags on Empornium, but in doing so the system has been refined in an effort to make them more useful. The system implemented is \'Community Tagging\'. However, like all tagging systems this wont work without all members assistance.\r\n\r\nTags were a favourite among many of the old Cheggit members BUT, those members will notice the tag system employed here is slightly different to Cheggits. As the name implies, Community Tagging has more direct member input, and there is an expectation by Empornium on its members to use them correctly. Empornium also employs a traditional [url=http://empornium.mooo.com/articles.php?topic=search]Torrent Search[/url] system too, and even that one is more advanced. \r\n\r\nThe end result is we get the best of both worlds and then some. The opportunity to use each of the search functions in concert with each other is a major bonus and can help to refine a search much more narrowly. But this can only work if all members understand the concepts and use them in a manner that is intended. So remember that, our use of the Community Tag system can be a great benefit, or an abject failure, and that depends entirely on us ...the members.\r\n\r\nWhile tags are not a mandatory aspect of a torrent, they are implemented so it makes sense to make use of them.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[size=3][b]Tag Tools[/b][/size]\r\n\r\nTo make scanning the tags of a particular torrent easier, the heading \'Tags\' on each torrent page is a toggle switch, and if clicked will switch the sorting method from \'vote count\' to \'alphabetical\'.\r\n\r\nBe aware of the [url=http://empornium.mooo.com/articles.php?topic=tag]Tagging Rules[/url]\r\n\r\nMake yourself familiar with the [url=http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?action=tag_synonyms]Official Tag List[/url]\r\n\r\nThe site is geared to recognise a synonym. That is if a member doing a search enters a common alternative to an official tag, the synonym system will offer them results with the official tag. So dont worry about all the alternatives.\r\n\r\nOn each torrent upload page, there is a drop down menu for official tags. There is no need to remember them all, or to keep switching between pages to use them. The drop down menu will list all official tags and you simply select the appropriate ones and they are added to your torrent. Easy.\r\n\r\nTag voting (+) or (-) and Tag adding. See the section below on \'Community Tagging\'\r\n\r\nTags Glossary, a list of possible tags.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[size=3][b]So what is a Tag?[/b][/size]\r\n\r\nA tag is a word or group of words that can be searched on in order to help users find content. It is not a title, or a description, it is a single word or a group of words joined by a period (\'.\') to assist in searches. i.e: small.tits or \'ebony\' etc. Its more inclusive and expansive than simple category systems which limited you to one category. The category system is also used here, tags are a supplement to that system. They are a method of informing people and the search system of each uploads unique aspects or \'kinks\'. What makes the clip unique or distinguishes it from the thousands of other uploads that also fit in the same category. You can add the single category, plus the aspects that individualise the clips you\'re uploading.\r\n\r\nExample, if a clip has an ebony lady with small tits you could tag it with, \'ebony small.tits\' (minus the quotes). Between individual tags there is a space, and a \'.\' (period) is used to join words that are part of an individual tag. small.tits big.cock big.tits etc.\r\n\r\nAnother example expanding on the ebony clip mentioned. \r\n - A clip may include a woman with small tits and a dude with a big cock, doing anal sex finishing with a facial. \r\n - The title may be, \'Halle Does Barry\', \r\n - Its category might be hardcore and \r\n - Its description may say \'Halle meets Barry for lunch, she gets more than she bargained for when Barry goes to town on her, and she loves every minute of it.\' \r\n\r\nThe limitation of that description is that it does not include the term small tits despite (at least one of) the actresses having small tits, and it may or may not have \'anal\', big cock\' or \'facial\' included in the description either. As a consequence, using the traditional search system that torrent would fail to appear in the results for ebony, anal, big cock, small tits or facial. It will only show up searching for things in the category, description or title. And many find typing full descriptions tiresome already. With the tags system this torrent could be uploaded as per the description already given, plus tagged with; anal big.cock small.tits facial ebony and any other specific aspect as well. However, these are not a substitute for a description, a reasonable description must still be supplied.\r\n\r\nWith those \'Tags\', if a member has a preference for ebony, small tits, big cocks, facials or anal, they could simply search using the tag \'small.tits\' ((without quote marks) or one or more of the other tags) and they should get a list of clips from all genres where at least one actress has small tits. (or whatever tag(s) they choose to search for).\r\n\r\nNow if you think about it, this can be beneficial as there are many \'indulgences\' or \'kinks\' that would rarely or at least not always form part of a description or title. Tags can help us find our particular \'bent\'. This is what is meant by unique.\r\n\r\nSo I hear you asking what if I tag my torrent correctly but members doing searches enter an alternative, wont they miss my torrent? i.e: big.tits, v big.knockers. You\'re partially right, we dont all call them the same thing. BUT we have it covered, just stick to the official tags. If a member enters big.knockers into the system on search, the synonym feature of the system will show them results for big.tits. You wont miss out on any hits.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[size=3][b]Community Tagging[/b][/size]\r\n\r\n\r\n[size=2][b]Voting and Adding Tags[/b][/size]\r\n\r\nWhen an uploader adds tags when making the torrent, they are given a count of 8, plus 1 for the uploaders vote. The idea is that 8 is a basis to help keep tags long enough for members to agree on them, and the uploader has no need to vote for tags they already added. However, if you prefer, this can be switched off in your settings. The tag will be added with just the 8 base votes.\r\n\r\nWhen a tag is added by members it is given a base count of 3 plus the one for the member that added it. So it will appear with 4, or 3 depending on your settings.\r\n\r\nFor the moment at least, interacting with other peoples tags is limited to those members with a status above \'Apprentice\'. We apologise to those who do not yet qualify, but that is necessary to limit the potential problems that can arise from inexperienced members. Of course an Apprentice can add tags to their own torrents during the upload.\r\n\r\n- If a tag is missing from someones torrent, and you KNOW it should be there then by all means add it. Theres no need to post in the comments section requesting the uploader or a mod to add it. All members above Apprentice can add tags to any torrent.\r\n\r\n- As the [url=http://empornium.mooo.com/articles.php?topic=tag]Tagging Rules[/url] state, members can vote a tag up, or down. If you agree that a tag is perfectly appropriate for the given torrent, then vote it up by clicking the (+) next to the relevant tag. If you believe in all fairness that the tag is wrong or misleading, then vote it down (-) next to the relevant tag.\r\n\r\n- Your vote is only counted once. But if you make a mistake on your vote, then you can correct it. Just click the opposite action and it will return to the state it was prior to the error. You can then click it again and apply your actual vote.\r\n\r\nThis aspect of Emporniums tagging system is important as it helps to limit the false positives when uploaders use useless or inappropriate tags, and it helps people find things when the uploader completely leaves them out. There are [url=http://empornium.mooo.com/articles.php?topic=tag]Tagging Rules[/url] regarding tags, so if you tag for hits, then you do so at your own risk. \r\n\r\nThe vote system also helps when the inevitable difference of opinion occurs. Not everyone considers tits for example in the same way. One persons small.tits will not qualify as small to another. The vote system allows for that difference based on a site wide attitude. It may not in the end reflect your own, or my, opinion, but it will be a site-wide consensus if we participate.\r\n\r\nAs per the rules, make sure your vote reflects the tag itself in relation to the content. Its pointless and damaging to the effectiveness of the system to vote a tag up just because the words give you a boner/hard nipple, and conversely pointless and damaging to vote down those that you find displeasing.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[size=3][b]So how can I as a member help?[/b][/size]\r\n\r\nBy all means, add tags, vote on tags. It is this participation that will make tags much more effective than simply leaving it up to the uploader alone. Voting and adding where appropriate is encouraged.\r\n\r\nTags serve two main purposes, searching for what you want and filtering out what you don\'t want. For this reason if you\'re going to add tags, or vote on them, it is important that you be as thorough as possible in your thinking. Try to think beyond the details that are important to you, and include the details that anyone else could possibly be interested in. There are tags that you care about that others don\'t, and tags others care about that you don\'t.\r\n\r\nFor, example you may have no interest in whether someone has bare feet or is wearing shoes. But there are people who only want to see one and not the other. Some people care about dialog more than sexual positions and others don\'t care about dialog at all but really care what specific sex acts are performed.\r\n\r\nFor tags to be as effective as possible, sometimes it is also important to tag the common as well as the unique. For example, you might think it\'s unimportant to tag big.cock because most male pornstars have big cocks and 99% of the videos meet this criteria. But suppose someone is looking for only videos with gay Asian men with big cocks. Without the big.cock tag that might be difficult to search for. Using those tags, the search becomes much more refined.\r\n\r\nThe efficiency of tags, tag search and the cloud relies on consistent tagging by everyone. Avoid essentially useless tags such as \r\n - ass, \r\n - boobs, \r\n - fuck, \r\n - sex, \r\n - hot.\r\nThese do not make useful search terms. These are useless tags.\r\n\r\nIn general every body part tag needs to have a qualifying adjective to be useful:  \r\n - small.ass\r\n - big.ass\r\n - small.tits,\r\n - big.tits\r\n - big.cock, \r\n - blue.eyes, \r\n - long.hair,\r\n - blonde.hair\r\n\r\nSame for acts:\r\n - slow.fuck\r\n - anal.sex\r\n\r\nThese things might make useful search terms to some members, and as such will help your torrent get more hits.\r\n\r\nHot? Its just an opinion. hot.ass is no better. It might be part of your description if you like, but shouldnt be a tag.\r\n\r\n\r\n[size=3][b]Creating Tags[/b][/size]\r\n\r\nIf it fits in with an official tag, you would be better off using that tag. You will get more hits that way and wont break the effectiveness of the tagging system.\r\n\r\nA list of suggestions and their explanation can be found in the Tags Glossary.\r\n\r\n\r\n[size=2][b]Allowable characters[/b][/size]\r\n\r\nLetters a-z\r\nNumbers 0-9\r\nPeriod (.) (used to string together multi-word tags (or should that be multi.word?))\r\n\r\n\r\n[size=2][b]Some Tips[/b][/size]\r\n\r\nit is beyond the scope of any tutorial to be exhaustive in creating tags so this is just a guide to give an idea of how its done. All tags created should have reference to all of the above information too. \r\n\r\nCreate a multi-word tag by using the dot as the separator. For example, to tag \"Chicks with Dicks\", the proper 3 word tag would be chicks.with.dicks. When adding tags to your torrents, it is recommended that you start with the more general, then add more specific descriptors.\r\n\r\nTo separate multiple tags you use a space. No commas, just the space.\r\n\r\nchicks.with.dicks big.tits big.cock\r\n\r\nSome ideas for non-official tags could include who\'s in the video, the production house, the country it was made in, the language, year of release. Maybe its where they do it, or how they do it, what they express in the video. Essentially, what makes this video unique.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','2012-09-28 08:56:28'),(60,1,6,'collagehelp',0,'How to use Collages','A guide to collages of torrents','<< insert guide on what they are for... how permissins work... personal collages for higher ranks etc >>\r\n','2012-08-10 23:03:29'),(61,1,6,'stylesheets',0,'Stylesheets','How to change the site stylesheet (like a skin), or use an external css file','<<insert guide here>>','2012-08-10 23:03:13'),(62,2,1,'connchecker',0,'ConnChecker page content','this content is displayed as a help on the conn-checker page','The Connectability Checker is used to check you are connectable through your torrent client.\r\n\r\nYou must enter your external IP address and the port you are [size=2][color=#FF0000][b]currently connected[/b][/color][/size] on with your torrent client.\r\n\r\n[spoiler=Click to see examples of how to find your port in your torrent client]\r\n[align=center][b]uTorrent[/b]\r\n[img]http://www.freeimage.us/image-F4B4_50259EFA.jpg[/img]\r\n \r\n[b]Deluge[/b]\r\n[img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image-DED0_507EEDCA.jpg[/img][/align]\r\n\r\n\r\n[color=green][insert images of how to find the port you are using with various torrent clients.]This is work to be done[/color]\r\n[/spoiler]\r\n\r\n(If the Port is already filled in the site has got this info from your recent connection to the tracker - usually this will be correct)\r\n','2012-10-17 19:50:49'),(63,2,1,'tagrulesinline',0,'Tag rules for display on the upload page','basically just the tag rules article without the header','[*]Tags should be separated by a space, and you should use a period (\'.\') to separate words inside a tag - eg. [b][color=green]big.tits[/color][/b]. \r\n[*]There is a list of official tags and synonyms [url=/torrents.php?action=tag_synonyms]listed here[/url]. Please use these tags instead of \'unofficial\' tags (eg. use the official [b][color=green]big.tits[/color][/b] tag, instead of an unofficial [b][color=red]big.knockers[/color][/b] tag.)\r\n[*]Avoid using multiple synonymous tags. The synonym replacer will swap many for an official tag anyway, and if not then using both [b][color=red]redhair[/color][/b] and [b][color=red]red.head[/color][/b] is redundant and annoying - just use the official [b][color=green]redhead[/color][/b] tag. \r\n[*][b][size=2][u]Do[/u][/size][/b] add or vote up tags that describe the content well, and [b][size=2][u]do[/u][/size][/b] vote down tags that are inappropriate for that upload.\r\n[*][b][size=2][u]Don\'t[/u][/size][/b] use useless tags, such as [b][color=red]amazing.body[/color][/b], [b][color=red]awesome[/color][/b], [b][color=red]must.see[/color][/b]. Tags should describe the content of the upload in searchable keywords, not your opinion about the content. \r\n[*][b][size=2][u]Don\'t[/u][/size][/b] vote for tags because you like or dislike the content, voting should be about whether the tag is appropriate, not whether you like the scene.\r\n[*][b][size=2][u]Don\'t[/u][/size][/b] make comments in the comment section regarding tags. If you dont agree with a tag, vote it down or use the report function.\r\n[*][b][size=2][u]Don\'t[/u][/size][/b] recommend tags for uploaders to add in comments, think about the tag you propose, and if appropriate just add them yourself.','2012-08-02 02:39:43'),(64,1,5,'tag_glossary',0,'Tags -  Glossary','A list of potential tags for use and their meanings.','[center][color=#0261a3][size=5][font=Arial Black]List of possible tags[/font][/size][/color][/center]\r\n\r\nPlease note that this list is in no way complete so if you feel the need to add other tags to your torrent feel free to do this. We however ask you to only use tags for something that is actually present in the video. Abuse of this freedom in tagging but adding a lot of bad tags can result in having your upload rights revoked.\r\n\r\n\r\n[size=3][b]Some common tags[/b][/size]\r\n\r\nBelow is a list of tags, taken mostly from the now defunct Cheggit site. Some tags can be considered to be subcategories or sub-tags of another tag. For example - deepthroat is a subcategory of blowjob.  This list is far from complete and should not be considered authoritative, but it should should give you a good starting point.\r\n\r\nThey are grouped into categories to assist in finding the right tag idea, from the vast list.\r\n\r\nThe categories are;\r\n[*][b]Source[/b]\r\n[*][b]Gender and Sexual Orientation Related[/b]\r\n[*][b]Performer Origins Characteristics[/b]\r\n[*][b]Age Related[/b]\r\n[*][b]Physical Characteristics[/b]\r\n[*][b]Body Art[/b]\r\n[*][b]Positions and Acts[/b]\r\n[*][b]Descriptors[/b]\r\n[*][b]Ejaculation[/b]\r\n[*][b]Taboos, Force, Domination and Exhibitionism[/b]\r\n[*][b]Variations of manual manipulation[/b]\r\n[*][b]Oral[/b]\r\n[*][b]Roleplay, Bondage and Voyeurism[/b]\r\n[*][b]Other Kinks[/b]\r\n\r\n\r\n[b]Source Information[/b]\r\n\r\n[*]amateur - non-professional model and/or performer. May be professionally produced.\r\n[*]home.made - do-it-yourself. self-shot porn. Shot primarily for the use of the performers and is usually amateur in nature.\r\n[*]classic - landmark titles in the history of porn. A film judged over a period of decades to be of the highest quality. A perfect example of a particular style, something of lasting worth or with a timeless quality. It is generally accepted that Classic pron fits in an era between the mid 1960\'s to the end of the 80\'s. Others argue it includes the 90\'s too. It also has some overlap with vintage, which is stuff older than classic.\r\n[*]vintage - old. Referring to something from the past of high quality. In porn terms - anything that survives from the pre-vhs years would be considered vintage.\r\n[*]english - spoken language or language of origin\r\n[*]production house - tag the name of the production house of the release. i.e.: bangbros empire or whatever it is. Remember to use the period (\'.\') to separate words within a single tag.\r\n\r\n\r\n[b]Gender and Sexual Orientation Related[/b]\r\n\r\n[*]straight - man on woman action. Plain old vanilla porn.\r\n[*]gay - homosexuality. man on man.\r\n[*]twink - a gay slang term describing a young or young-looking gay man (in his late teens or early twenties) with a slender build, little or no body hair, and no facial hair (often referred to as a \"swimmer\'s build\" ). Used exclusively with a young gay male. The gay-male equivalent of a lolita\r\n[*]bear - a bear can generally be described as gay or bi lumberjack. Bears tend to be post-teen in age and have hairy bodies and facial hair - some are heavy-set or of a muscular build. They are the body opposite of a twink.\r\n[*]frottage - a form of non-penetrative male/male sex that usually but not always involves direct penis-to-penis contact.\r\n[*]lesbian - homosexuality. woman on woman. A girl-on-girl scene not including any male participants. May be used for a lesbian scene, in a mixed scene video/collection.\r\n[*]girl.on.girl - girl-on-girl action, it may be part of a video which has a mix of straight and lesbian content.\r\n[*]all.girl - a complete movie in which the only penis in sight is plastic. An all.girl film has exclusively lesbian content. Used with the lesbian tag.\r\n[*]tribbing - tribadism or tribbing, commonly known by its scissoring aspect, is a form of non-penetrative lesbian sex in which a woman rubs her vulva against her partner\'s body for sexual stimulation. Female on female sex.\r\n[*]hermaphrodite - the third sex. Persons with both male and female genitalia. Persons who are neither male nor female.\r\n[*]futanari - hermaphrodite found in japanese / animated porn and manga.\r\n[*]shemale - A person who has female identity and appearance, but has a penis. Shemale interactions can be tagged by type: shemale.on.shemale, shemale.on.male, shemale.on.female, male.on.shemale and female.on.shemale (usually with a strapon)\r\n[*]ladyboy - lolita transsexuals. A young, petite shemale.\r\n[*]transvestite - a person who dresses and acts in a style or manner traditionally associated with the opposite sex. Men who dress and act like women. Women who dress and act like men. Most transvestites are not homosexuals, however. Unlike transsexuals, a transvestite\'s change in appearance from male to female (or female to male) is due solely to costume, make-up, and prosthetics (eg, padded bra).\r\n[*]pegging - the practice in which a woman penetrates a man\'s anus with a strap-on dildo.\r\n\r\n\r\n[b]Performer Origins Characteristics[/b]\r\n\r\n[*]asian - from asia. Generally from japan, china, thailand, philippin