INSERT INTO `news` VALUES (1,1243,'Welcome Tester!','  :welcome3: \r\n\r\nThank you for helping us test the new beta tracker!\r\n\r\n[b]Use the site[/b]\r\n- The only way to find bugs is for you to use the test site. Make uploads, grab torrents, bookmark stuff, make posts, subscribe, look at your user history, report stuff (you can make bogus reports etc for testing), test everything! [b]It would be great if you could start a few of your old torrents too help us out with testing the tracker for a few days too.[/b]\r\n\r\n[b]We like bug reports[/b] :chase: \r\n- If you find something that you think is wrong, report it! Look for any previous identical reports and add it to an appropriate thread if it already exists, otherwise make a new thread in the bug forum. We would rather have duplicate reports than miss something! Bug reports dont have to be actual software bugs, anything you dont understand or think needs better explaining tell us, anything you think needs changing tell us, we may not agree but we do want all opinions :D\r\n\r\n[b]What happens on the test tracker stays on the test tracker![/b]  :shutup2: \r\n- Meaning that all stats on the test tracker will be wiped out when we go live. Therefore anything downloaded, uploaded, credits gained/spent, anything and everything to do with individual user stats and torrents will be reset to the current main site stats when we go live.\r\n\r\n[b]Don\'t worry about old and dead torrents etc[/b] \r\n- The test site has had the current data from the main site imported. As there are no seeders on the test site announce url currently the torrents will look dead. This is not a bug just a consequence of importing the current data.\r\n\r\n[b]Just remember that this server is running on very limited hardware, it\'s just for testing so please forgive us if it feels slow from time to time.[/b]\r\n :weakbench: \r\n\r\n','2012-07-03 23:11:10'),(2,1243,'New Server!','We have moved the test tracker to a new server. This way things should feel a lot more snappier and it will allow us to invite more testers! I you find anything that doesn\'t work as it did before, then send us a note and we\'ll take a look at it.\r\n\r\n :strongbench: ','2012-07-11 07:50:30'),(3,47234,'Welcum to the new batch of testers','I just finished Inviting another 50 testers here.  Please use the site and see what breaks.  This has basically doubled the number of users on the beta site so hopefully we start to see more action all around :)\r\n\r\nTo our new testers please drop into the forums and use/explore the site some.\r\n\r\nJust remember\r\n\r\n[b]What happens on the test tracker stays on the test tracker! :shutup2: [/b]\r\n\r\nThat includes not sharing where we hid the site :wink:\r\n\r\n[b]Update[/b] Invited another 201 testers yesterday plus i think a few random invites are being handed out.  So we should see more action here :)','2012-07-13 17:14:44'),(5,48010,'The Mods are now modding','Hi all testers,\r\n\r\nYes we have been a little slack but now we are starting to Mod the site like we do Emp.me when we have time\r\n\r\n[b]Don\'t say you weren\'t warned[/b]\r\n\r\n[color=blue]We are testing the report system now so it\'s like the main site[/color]\r\n\r\nPoor descriptions will be warned or nuked - please up a crap upload just so we can nuke it or add a report for you to change it\r\n\r\nNeed to test dupes too - again someone upload one and mark it \"Test Dupe\" so we don\'t have to search through all the torrents\r\n\r\nStart leeching - we need to be sure the stats work - report any problems with your client (screenshots will help)\r\n\r\nTest the Slots for DS and FL on torrents and the Bouns shop too - if you need slots or credits see here [url=http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2679]request slots or credits[/url]\r\n\r\nReport stuff even if not real\r\n\r\nThanks - Dave and the other Staff who are testing','2012-07-25 22:33:17'),(6,171777,'Guide to bug hunting','This guide is also a sticky in the forums in the bugs section ([url=http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=3012]link![/url]).\r\n\r\n[size=3][b]Guide to effective bug testing[/b][/size]\r\n\r\nThis guide is meant to be a good starting point for any tester. It contains some basic guidelines to testing and bug hunting aswell as some things that we already found. If you think that this guide is not complete or if it is incorrect please send me a PM or reply in this thread.\r\n\r\n[size=3][b]How to submit a bug report[/b][/size]\r\n\r\nLet\'s start with the most important information first. What do do when you find a bug. \r\n\r\nTo tell us about it we need specific information:\r\n\r\n\r\nNow for some simple guidelines when you want to share you bug with the coders.\r\n \r\n[*]Search the forum to see if the bug is already known.\r\n[*]If the bug is indeed new then start a new topic. As a topic name please use following: Location - Desription of bug. With location I mean things like [Forum] or [Torrent Details]. Example: [Torrent Upload] - My cover image is not accepted.\r\n[*]Fill the topic with as much information as you possibly can. Use images if it is hard to describe what is happening. Be sure to atleast give the information as noted in the following 3 bullets.\r\n[*][b]The page url[/b] For example the url for the browse torrents page is [code]http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php[/code] which when written in a post becomes: http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php\r\n[*][b]What is wrong[/b] Tell us what the problem is, and if applicable the way you expect it to work.\r\n[*][b]How to reproduce it[/b] Please include enough information so that we can reproduce the bug ourselves. Reproduce it yourself first if possible, and make a note of what actions produce the bug.\r\n[*]Keep track of your topic (potentially subscribe to it). Coders might require additional information or another tester might want to do additional tests working together with you.\r\n \r\n[size=3][b]How to hunt for bugs[/b][/size]\r\n \r\nThere is no set way in which one can hunt for a bug. The reason for this is that no one knows where the bugs are located. There are however a few simple pointers that you can follow while hunting:\r\n \r\n[*][b]Work systematically[/b] In other words don\'t go clicking haphazardly because that way it is almost impossible to reproduce what you did when things go wrong.\r\n[*][b]Test things multiple times[/b] A result could always be a fluke. This goes for both bugs and correct functionality. If you test something several times and the same thing always happens then you either have a bug that you can reproduce or you have correct behaviour that you can vouch for.\r\n[*][b]Test again at a later time[/b] Some bugs are easy to fix, others are a lot more complicated. To ensure that a bug is truly gone or that an old bug doesn\'t reappear it is always advisable to test features again a week later and yet again the next week. It would suck if 2 weeks after going live a bug reappears because it  is date triggered and happens every 2 weeks or something.\r\n[*][b]Don\'t assume anything[/b] As they say: \"Assumption is the mother of all fuck-ups\". If you think something works then please make sure that it does.\r\n \r\n \r\nPlease note that this list probably is not complete and is therefor subject to change. Take a look every once in a while to see if there were changes. Who knows the coders might have noticed that a certain step is not neccessary and you are still doing all that work for nothing! ','2012-08-15 10:01:38'),(7,47234,'We are on the Home stretch.  Site in feature lock','Ok guys no more bugging the coders with Suggestions that time has passed.\r\n\r\nThe site is now one step closer to done.  Feature lock has been declared.  Its now time to hunt bugs and find the last few.\r\n\r\nI have closed the Suggestions forum.\r\n\r\nClownius\r\n\r\nWe really need all our testers to go all out on using the site now to see what if any bugs they can find.\r\n\r\n  :bugchases:  :bugchases: :chase:  :chase: ','2012-08-17 15:39:50'),(8,84499,'WARNING: testing awards scheduler again','\r\nI have made some changes to the masspm code fired by the awards scheduler and changed the timings and turned it back on for load testing.\r\n\r\nThis means a lot of you will be getting annoying PM\'s, and I may have to reset it and run it again (which means wiping the user badges data as well) so you may well be seeing badges appearing and dissappearing and messages queing up in your inboxes over the next 24-48 hours.\r\n\r\nOnce I am done I will automagically remove all the system messages you have been sent so you can ignore them if you want and they will go away at some point anyway.\r\n\r\nThanks for your patience :smile1:\r\n\r\n- mifune.','2012-08-26 15:44:33'),(9,84499,'Testing credit award system','I am testing a new query for awarding credits... you may get some strange amounts of extra credits as I manually run queries to benchmark various options so dont be alarmed.\r\n\r\n[b]finished[/b] - its possible I may have booted various real seeders during the tests... if that is the case sorry  :innocent: - hopefullly the tracker reconnected you fairly quickly.\r\n\r\nit was in a good cause... the credit query is now finalised and despite being a little more complex is about 30% faster than the previous version  :D \r\n \r\n\r\n','2012-08-30 23:28:31'),(10,84499,'Client Whitelist is in action','\r\nFor testing purposes I have enabled the client whitelist.\r\n\r\nYou can see which clients are whitelisted here: [url=/articles.php?topic=clients]Clients Article[/url]\r\n\r\nWe have a nice long list of several hundred clients that we will be adding to the whitelist but its going to take us a few days to remove the bad clients and get it sorted.\r\n\r\nIn the meantime if you want your client added to the list pronto so you can upload and download here please post in [url=/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=3078&page=1]this thread[/url] and an admin will add it to whitelist asap (no asking for bitcomet/bitlord other banned clients though!).','2012-09-02 22:05:31');
/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `news` ENABLE KEYS */;
UNLOCK TABLES;

